47  private static void emitGasCheck(BoogieStmtList newBody)
48  {
49  BoogieStmtList thenBody = new BoogieStmtList();
50  thenBody.AddStatement(new BoogieReturnCmd());
51 
52  newBody.AddStatement(new BoogieIfCmd(
53  new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.LT, new BoogieIdentifierExpr("gas"),
54  new BoogieLiteralExpr(0)), thenBody, null));
55  }
56 
57  private void preTranslationAction(ASTNode node)
58  {
59  if (context.TranslateFlags.InstrumentGas)
60  {
61  // Some times solc will give a positive gas cost to some "weird" (i.e., outside a transaction or function) nodes.
62  if (node.GasCost > 0 && currentStmtList != null)
63  // gas := gas - node.GasCost
64  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(new BoogieIdentifierExpr("gas"),
65  new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.SUB, new BoogieIdentifierExpr("gas"), new BoogieLiteralExpr(node.GasCost))));
66 
67  if (context.TranslateFlags.ModelReverts)
68  {
69  if (node is Continue)
70  {
71  emitGasCheck(currentStmtList);
72  }
73  }
74  }
75  }

77  public ProcedureTranslator(TranslatorContext context, bool _genInlineAttrsInBpl = true)
78  {
79  this.context = context;
80  boogieToLocalVarsMap = new Dictionary<string, List<BoogieVariable>>();
81  genInlineAttrsInBpl = _genInlineAttrsInBpl;
82  contractInvariants = new Dictionary<string, List<BoogieExpr>>();

85  public override bool Visit(ContractDefinition node)
86  {
87  preTranslationAction(node);
88 
89  currentContract = node;
90 
91  if (currentContract.ContractKind == EnumContractKind.LIBRARY &&
92  currentContract.Name.Equals("VeriSol"))
93  return true;
94 
95  // generate default empty constructor if there is no constructor explicitly defined
96  if (!context.IsConstructorDefined(node))
97  {
98  GenerateDefaultConstructor(node);
99  }
100 
101  foreach (ASTNode child in node.Nodes)
102  {
103  if (child is VariableDeclaration varDecl)
104  {
105  TranslateStateVarDeclaration(varDecl);
106  }
107  else if (child is StructDefinition structDefn)
108  {
109  TranslateStructDefinition(structDefn);
110  }
111  else
112  {
113  child.Accept(this);
114  }
115  }
116 
117  return false;
118  }
119 
120  private void TranslateStructDefinition(StructDefinition structDefn)
121  {
122  foreach(var member in structDefn.Members)
123  {
124  VeriSolAssert(!member.TypeDescriptions.IsStruct(),
125  "Do no handle nested structs yet!");
126  var type = TransUtils.GetBoogieTypeFromSolidityTypeName(member.TypeName);
127  var mapType = new BoogieMapType(BoogieType.Ref, type);
128  var mapName = member.Name + "_" + structDefn.CanonicalName;
129  context.Program.AddDeclaration(new BoogieGlobalVariable(new BoogieTypedIdent(mapName, mapType)));
130  }
131  }
132 
133  private void TranslateStateVarDeclaration(VariableDeclaration varDecl)
134  {
135  VeriSolAssert(varDecl.StateVariable, $"{varDecl} is not a state variable");
136 
137  string name = TransUtils.GetCanonicalStateVariableName(varDecl, context);
138  BoogieType type = TransUtils.GetBoogieTypeFromSolidityTypeName(varDecl.TypeName);
139  BoogieMapType mapType = new BoogieMapType(BoogieType.Ref, type);
140 
141  // Issue a warning for intXX variables in case /useModularArithemtic option is used:
142  if (context.TranslateFlags.UseModularArithmetic && varDecl.TypeDescriptions.IsInt())
143  {
144  Console.WriteLine($"Warning: signed integer arithmetic is not handled with /useModularArithmetic option");
145  }
146 
147  if (varDecl.TypeName is Mapping)
148  {
149  context.Program.AddDeclaration(new BoogieGlobalVariable(new BoogieTypedIdent(name, mapType)));
150  }
151  else if (varDecl.TypeName is ArrayTypeName)
152  {
153  //array variables can be assigned
154  context.Program.AddDeclaration(new BoogieGlobalVariable(new BoogieTypedIdent(name, mapType)));
155  }
156  else // other type of state variables
157  {
158  context.Program.AddDeclaration(new BoogieGlobalVariable(new BoogieTypedIdent(name, mapType)));
159  }
160  }

162  public override bool Visit(EnumDefinition node)
163  {
164  preTranslationAction(node);
165  // do nothing
166  return false;
167  }

169  private BoogieCallCmd InstrumentForPrintingData(TypeDescription type, BoogieExpr value, string name)
170  {
171  // don't emit the instrumentation
172  if (context.TranslateFlags.NoDataValuesInfoFlag)
173  return null;
174 
175  if (type.IsDynamicArray() || type.IsStaticArray())
176  return null;
177 
178  if (type.IsAddress() || type.IsContract())
179  {
180  // Skipping dynamic and static array types:
181  var callCmd = new BoogieCallCmd("boogie_si_record_sol2Bpl_ref", new List<BoogieExpr>() { value }, new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>());
182  callCmd.Attributes = new List<BoogieAttribute>();
183  callCmd.Attributes.Add(new BoogieAttribute("cexpr", $"\"{name}\""));
184  return callCmd;
185  }
186  else if (type.IsInt() || type.IsUint() || type.IsString() || type.IsBytes())
187  // TypeString.StartsWith("uint") || type.TypeString.StartsWith("int") || type.TypeString.StartsWith("string ") || type.TypeString.StartsWith("bytes"))
188  {
189  var callCmd = new BoogieCallCmd("boogie_si_record_sol2Bpl_int", new List<BoogieExpr>() { value }, new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>());
190  callCmd.Attributes = new List<BoogieAttribute>();
191  callCmd.Attributes.Add(new BoogieAttribute("cexpr", $"\"{name}\""));
192  return callCmd;
193  }
194  else if (type.IsBool())
195  {
196  var callCmd = new BoogieCallCmd("boogie_si_record_sol2Bpl_bool", new List<BoogieExpr>() { value }, new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>());
197  callCmd.Attributes = new List<BoogieAttribute>();
198  callCmd.Attributes.Add(new BoogieAttribute("cexpr", $"\"{name}\""));
199  return callCmd;
200  }
201 
202  return null;
203  }

206  private void PrintArguments(FunctionDefinition node, List<BoogieVariable> inParams, BoogieStmtList currentStmtList)
207  {
208  // Print dummy first parameter (as a delimeter for parsing corral.txt):
209  TypeDescription addrType = new TypeDescription();
210  addrType.TypeString = "bool";
211  // There's no BoogieLiteralExpr that accepts ref type:
212  //BoogieConstant nullConst = new BoogieConstant(new BoogieTypedIdent("null", BoogieType.Ref), true);
213  var callCmd = InstrumentForPrintingData(addrType, new BoogieLiteralExpr(false), "_verisolFirstArg");
214  if (callCmd != null)
215  {
216  currentStmtList.AddStatement(callCmd);
217  }
218 
219  // Add default parameters "this", "msg.sender", "msg.value"
220  addrType = new TypeDescription();
221  addrType.TypeString = "address";
222  callCmd = InstrumentForPrintingData(addrType, new BoogieIdentifierExpr(inParams[0].Name), "this");
223  if (callCmd != null)
224  {
225  currentStmtList.AddStatement(callCmd);
226  }
227  callCmd = InstrumentForPrintingData(addrType, new BoogieIdentifierExpr(inParams[1].Name), "msg.sender");
228  if (callCmd != null)
229  {
230  currentStmtList.AddStatement(callCmd);
231  }
232  var valType = new TypeDescription();
233  valType.TypeString = "int";
234  callCmd = InstrumentForPrintingData(valType, new BoogieIdentifierExpr(inParams[2].Name), "msg.value");
235  if (callCmd != null)
236  {
237  currentStmtList.AddStatement(callCmd);
238  }
239 
240  // when we call this for an implicit constructor, we don't have a node, which
241  // implies there are no parameters
242  if (node == null)
243  {
244  // Print dummy last parameter (as a delimeter for parsing corral.txt):
245  addrType = new TypeDescription();
246  addrType.TypeString = "bool";
247  callCmd = InstrumentForPrintingData(addrType, new BoogieLiteralExpr(true), "_verisolLastArg");
248  if (callCmd != null)
249  {
250  currentStmtList.AddStatement(callCmd);
251  }
252  return;
253  }
254 
255  foreach (VariableDeclaration param in node.Parameters.Parameters)
256  {
257  var parType = param.TypeDescriptions != null ? param.TypeDescriptions : null;
258  int parIndex = node.Parameters.Parameters.IndexOf(param);
259  BoogieVariable parVar = inParams[parIndex + 3];
260  string parName = param.Name;
261  var parExpr = new BoogieIdentifierExpr(parVar.Name);
262  callCmd = InstrumentForPrintingData(parType, parExpr, parName);
263  if (callCmd != null)
264  {
265  currentStmtList.AddStatement(callCmd);
266  }
267  }
268  // Print dummy last parameter (as a delimeter for parsing corral.txt):
269  addrType = new TypeDescription();
270  addrType.TypeString = "bool";
271  callCmd = InstrumentForPrintingData(addrType, new BoogieLiteralExpr(true), "_verisolLastArg");
272  if (callCmd != null)
273  {
274  currentStmtList.AddStatement(callCmd);
275  }
276  }
277  public override bool Visit(FunctionDefinition node)
278  {
279  preTranslationAction(node);
280  // VeriSolAssert(node.IsConstructor || node.Modifiers.Count <= 1, "Multiple Modifiers are not supported yet");
281  VeriSolAssert(currentContract != null);
282 
283  currentFunction = node;
284 
285  // procedure name
286  string procName = node.Name + "_" + currentContract.Name;
287 
288  if (node.IsConstructor)
289  {
290  procName += "_NoBaseCtor";
291  }
292  currentBoogieProc = procName;
293 
294  // input parameters
295  List<BoogieVariable> inParams = TransUtils.GetDefaultInParams();
296  // initialize statement list to include assumption about parameter types
297  currentStmtList = new BoogieStmtList();
298  // get all formal input parameters
299  node.Parameters.Accept(this);
300  inParams.AddRange(currentParamList);
301 
302  // Print function argument values to corral.txt for counterexample:
303  PrintArguments(node, inParams, currentStmtList);
304 
305  // output parameters
306  isReturnParameterList = true;
307  node.ReturnParameters.Accept(this);
308  isReturnParameterList = false;
309  List<BoogieVariable> outParams = currentParamList;
310 
311  var assumesForParamsAndReturn = currentStmtList;
312  currentStmtList = new BoogieStmtList();
313 
314  // attributes
315  List<BoogieAttribute> attributes = new List<BoogieAttribute>();
316  if ((node.Visibility == EnumVisibility.PUBLIC || node.Visibility == EnumVisibility.EXTERNAL)
317  && !node.IsConstructor
318  && !node.IsFallback) //don't expose fallback for calling directly
319  {
320  attributes.Add(new BoogieAttribute("public"));
321  }
322  // generate inline attribute for a function only when /noInlineAttrs is specified
323  if (genInlineAttrsInBpl)
324  attributes.Add(new BoogieAttribute("inline", 1));
325 
326  if (currentContract.ContractKind == EnumContractKind.LIBRARY &&
327  currentContract.Name.Equals("VeriSol"))
328  {
329  return false;
330  }
331  // we add any pre/post conditions after analyzing the boy later
332  BoogieProcedure procedure = new BoogieProcedure(procName, inParams, outParams, attributes);
333  context.Program.AddDeclaration(procedure);
334 
335  // could be just a declaration
336  if (!node.Implemented)
337  {
338  return false;
339  }
340 
341  // skip if it in ignored set
342  if (context.IsMethodInIgnoredSet(node, currentContract))
343  {
344  Console.WriteLine($"Warning!: Ignoring method {node.Name} in contract {currentContract.Name} specified using /ignoreMethod:");
345  }
346  else
347  {
348  // local variables and function body
349  // TODO: move to earlier
350  boogieToLocalVarsMap[currentBoogieProc] = new List<BoogieVariable>();
351 
352  // TODO: each local array variable should be distinct and 0 initialized
353 
354  BoogieStmtList procBody = new BoogieStmtList();
355  currentPostlude = new BoogieStmtList();
356 
357 
358  // Add possible assume statements from parameters
359  procBody.AppendStmtList(assumesForParamsAndReturn);
360 
361  // if payable, then modify the balance
362  if (node.StateMutability == EnumStateMutability.PAYABLE)
363  {
364  procBody.AddStatement(new BoogieCommentCmd("---- Logic for payable function START "));
365  var balnSender = new BoogieMapSelect(new BoogieIdentifierExpr("Balance"), new BoogieIdentifierExpr("msgsender_MSG"));
366  var balnThis = new BoogieMapSelect(new BoogieIdentifierExpr("Balance"), new BoogieIdentifierExpr("this"));
367  var msgVal = new BoogieIdentifierExpr("msgvalue_MSG");
368  //assume Balance[msg.sender] >= msg.value
369  procBody.AddStatement(new BoogieAssumeCmd(new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.GE, balnSender, msgVal)));
370  //balance[msg.sender] = balance[msg.sender] - msg.value
371  procBody.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(balnSender, new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.SUB, balnSender, msgVal)));
372  //balance[this] = balance[this] + msg.value
373  procBody.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(balnThis, new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.ADD, balnThis, msgVal)));
374  procBody.AddStatement(new BoogieCommentCmd("---- Logic for payable function END "));
375  }
376 
377  // if (node.Modifiers.Count == 1)
378  for (int i = 0; i < node.Modifiers.Count; ++i)
379  {
380  var outVars = new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>();
381 
382  // insert call to modifier prelude
383  if (context.ModifierToBoogiePreImpl.ContainsKey(node.Modifiers[i].ModifierName.Name))
384  {
385  // local variables declared in the prelude of a modifier (before _ ) becomes out variables and then in parameters of postlude
386  foreach (var localVar in context.ModifierToPreludeLocalVars[node.Modifiers[i].ModifierName.ToString()])
387  {
388  var outVar = new BoogieLocalVariable(new BoogieTypedIdent("__mod_out_" + localVar.Name, localVar.TypedIdent.Type));
389  boogieToLocalVarsMap[currentBoogieProc].Add(outVar);
390  outVars.Add(new BoogieIdentifierExpr(outVar.Name));
391  }
392 
393  List<BoogieExpr> arguments = TransUtils.GetDefaultArguments();
394  if (node.Modifiers[i].Arguments != null)
395  arguments.AddRange(node.Modifiers[i].Arguments.ConvertAll(TranslateExpr));
396  string callee = node.Modifiers[i].ModifierName.ToString() + "_pre";
397  var callCmd = new BoogieCallCmd(callee, arguments, outVars);
398  procBody.AddStatement(callCmd);
399  }
400 
401  // insert call to modifier postlude
402  if (context.ModifierToBoogiePostImpl.ContainsKey(node.Modifiers[i].ModifierName.Name))
403  {
404  List<BoogieExpr> arguments = TransUtils.GetDefaultArguments();
405  if (node.Modifiers[i].Arguments != null)
406  arguments.AddRange(node.Modifiers[i].Arguments.ConvertAll(TranslateExpr));
407  arguments.AddRange(outVars.Select(x => new BoogieIdentifierExpr(x.Name)));
408  string callee = node.Modifiers[i].ModifierName.ToString() + "_post";
409  var callCmd = new BoogieCallCmd(callee, arguments, null);
410  currentPostlude.AddStatement(callCmd);
411  }
412  }
413 
414  try
415  {
416  procBody.AppendStmtList(TranslateStatement(node.Body));
417  }
418  catch (NotImplementedException e)
419  {
420  // In case of an inline assembly in the body of the function, do not emit procedure body (aka implementation):
421  if (e.Message.Equals("inline assembly"))
422  {
423  inlineAssemblyPresent = true;
424  }
425  else
426  {
427  throw e;
428  }
429  }
430 
431  // add modifier postlude call if function body has no return
432  if (currentPostlude != null)
433  {
434  procBody.AppendStmtList(currentPostlude);
435  currentPostlude = null;
436  }
437 
438  // initialization statements
439  if (node.IsConstructor)
440  {
441  BoogieStmtList oldCurrentStmtList = currentStmtList;
442  currentStmtList = new BoogieStmtList();
443  BoogieStmtList initStmts;
444  GenerateInitializationStmts(currentContract);
445  initStmts = currentStmtList;
446  currentStmtList = oldCurrentStmtList;
447  initStmts.AppendStmtList(procBody);
448  procBody = initStmts;
449  }
450 
451  // is it a VeriSol Contract Invariant function?
452  List<BoogieExpr> contractInvs = null;
453  if (IsVeriSolContractInvariantFunction(node, procBody, out contractInvs))
454  {
455  //add contract invs as loop invariants to outer loop
456  VeriSolAssert(!contractInvariants.ContainsKey(currentContract.Name), $"More than one function defining the contract invariant for contract {currentContract.Name}");
457  contractInvariants[currentContract.Name] = contractInvs;
458  }
459  else
460  {
461  //extract the specifications from within the body
462  BoogieStmtList procBodyWoRequires, procBodyWoEnsures, procBodyWoModifies;
463  var preconditions = ExtractSpecifications("Requires_VeriSol", procBody, out procBodyWoRequires);
464  var postconditions = ExtractSpecifications("Ensures_VeriSol", procBodyWoRequires, out procBodyWoEnsures);
465  var modifies = ExtractSpecifications("Modifies_VeriSol", procBodyWoEnsures, out procBodyWoModifies);
466 
467  procedure.AddPreConditions(preconditions);
468  procedure.AddPostConditions(postconditions);
469  procedure.AddPostConditions(modifies);
470  List<BoogieVariable> localVars = boogieToLocalVarsMap[currentBoogieProc];
471  if (!inlineAssemblyPresent)
472  {
473  BoogieImplementation impelementation = new BoogieImplementation(procName, inParams, outParams, localVars, procBodyWoModifies);
474  context.Program.AddDeclaration(impelementation);
475  }
476  else
477  {
478  inlineAssemblyPresent = false;
479  }
480  }
481  }
482 
483  // generate real constructors
484  if (node.IsConstructor)
485  {
486  GenerateConstructorWithBaseCalls(node, inParams);
487  }
488 
489  return false;
490  }
491 
492  private bool IsVeriSolContractInvariantFunction(FunctionDefinition node, BoogieStmtList procBody, out List<BoogieExpr> contractInvs)
493  {
494  contractInvs = null;
495  if (node.Visibility != EnumVisibility.PRIVATE ||
496  node.StateMutability != EnumStateMutability.VIEW ||
497  node.Parameters.Parameters.Count != 0)
498  {
499  return false;
500  }
501 
502  contractInvs = ExtractContractInvariants(procBody);
503  return contractInvs.Count > 0;
504  }
505 
506  public override bool Visit(ModifierDefinition node)
507  {
508  preTranslationAction(node);
509  currentBoogieProc = node.Name + "_pre";
510  boogieToLocalVarsMap[currentBoogieProc] = new List<BoogieVariable>();
511 
512  Block body = node.Body;
513  BoogieStmtList prelude = new BoogieStmtList();
514  BoogieStmtList postlude = new BoogieStmtList();
515 
516  bool translatingPre = true;
517  bool hasPre = false;
518  bool hasPost = false;
519 
520  foreach (Statement statement in body.Statements)
521  {
522  if (statement is VariableDeclarationStatement)
523  {
524  // VeriSolAssert(false, "locals within modifiers not supported");
525  }
526  if (statement is PlaceholderStatement)
527  {
528  translatingPre = false;
529  // add __out_mod_x := x, for any local explicitly declared in the prelude
530  foreach(var localDeclared in context.ModifierToPreludeLocalVars[node.Name])
531  {
532  var lhsExpr = new BoogieIdentifierExpr("__out_mod_" + localDeclared.Name);
533  var rhsExpr = new BoogieIdentifierExpr(localDeclared.Name);
534  prelude.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(lhsExpr, rhsExpr));
535  }
536  currentBoogieProc = node.Name + "_post";
537  boogieToLocalVarsMap[currentBoogieProc] = new List<BoogieVariable>();
538  continue;
539  }
540  BoogieStmtList stmtList = TranslateStatement(statement);
541  if (translatingPre)
542  {
543  prelude.AppendStmtList(stmtList);
544  hasPre = true;
545  }
546  else
547  {
548  postlude.AppendStmtList(stmtList);
549  hasPost = true;
550  }
551  }
552 
553  // we are going to make any locals declared in prelude visible to postlude by making htem as output variables
554  // and making them input to the postlude
555  if (hasPre)
556  {
557  // removig this removes local declaration of temporaries introduced in translation
558  context.ModifierToBoogiePreImpl[node.Name].LocalVars = boogieToLocalVarsMap[node.Name + "_pre"];
559  // context.ModifierToBoogiePreImpl[node.Name].LocalVars = new List<BoogieVariable>();
560  context.ModifierToBoogiePreImpl[node.Name].StructuredStmts = prelude;
561  }
562  if (hasPost)
563  {
564  context.ModifierToBoogiePostImpl[node.Name].LocalVars = boogieToLocalVarsMap[node.Name + "_post"];
565  context.ModifierToBoogiePostImpl[node.Name].StructuredStmts = postlude;
566  }
567  return false;
568  }
569 
570  // generate the initialization statements for state variables
571  // assume message sender is not null
572  // assign null to other address variables
573  private BoogieStmtList GenerateInitializationStmts(ContractDefinition contract)
574  {
575  currentStmtList = new BoogieStmtList();
576  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieCommentCmd("start of initialization"));
577 
578  // assume msgsender_MSG != null;
579  BoogieExpr assumeLhs = new BoogieIdentifierExpr("msgsender_MSG");
580  BoogieExpr assumeExpr = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.NEQ, assumeLhs, new BoogieIdentifierExpr("null"));
581  BoogieAssumeCmd assumeCmd = new BoogieAssumeCmd(assumeExpr);
582  currentStmtList.AddStatement(assumeCmd);
583 
584  BoogieAssignCmd balanceInit =
585  new BoogieAssignCmd(
586  new BoogieMapSelect(new BoogieIdentifierExpr("Balance"), new BoogieIdentifierExpr("this")),
587  new BoogieLiteralExpr(0));
588  currentStmtList.AddStatement(balanceInit);
589 
590  foreach (VariableDeclaration varDecl in context.GetStateVarsByContract(contract))
591  {
592  // assign null to other address variables
593  if (varDecl.TypeName is ElementaryTypeName elementaryType)
594  {
595  GenerateInitializationForElementaryTypes(varDecl, elementaryType);
596  }
597 
598  //// false/0 initialize mappings, arrays and structs (one level)
599  if (varDecl.TypeName is Mapping mapping)
600  {
601  GenerateInitializationForMappingStateVar(varDecl, mapping);
602  }
603  else if (varDecl.TypeName is ArrayTypeName array)
604  {
605  GenerateInitializationForArrayStateVar(varDecl, array);
606  }
607  else if (varDecl.TypeName is UserDefinedTypeName structOrContract)
608  {
609  if (varDecl.TypeDescriptions.IsStruct())
610  GenerateInitializationForStructStateVar(varDecl, structOrContract);
611  }
612  }
613 
614 
615  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieCommentCmd("end of initialization"));
616 
617  // TODO: add the initializations outside of constructors
618 
619  return currentStmtList;
620  }
621 
622  private void GenerateInitializationForArrayStateVar(VariableDeclaration varDecl, ArrayTypeName array)
623  {
624  // Issue a warning for intXX type in case /useModularArithemtic option is used:
625  if (context.TranslateFlags.UseModularArithmetic && array.BaseType.ToString().StartsWith("int"))
626  {
627  Console.WriteLine($"Warning: signed integer arithmetic is not handled with /useModularArithmetic option");
628  }
629 
630  BoogieMapSelect lhsMap = CreateDistinctArrayMappingAddress(currentStmtList, varDecl);
631 
632  // lets also initialize the array Lengths (only for Arrays declared in this class)
633  var lengthMapSelect = new BoogieMapSelect(new BoogieIdentifierExpr("Length"), lhsMap);
634  var lengthExpr = array.Length == null ? new BoogieLiteralExpr(BigInteger.Zero) : TranslateExpr(array.Length);
635  // var lengthEqualsZero = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.EQ, lengthMapSelect, new BoogieLiteralExpr(0));
636  var lengthConstraint = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.EQ, lengthMapSelect, lengthExpr);
637  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssumeCmd(lengthConstraint));
638  }

687  private void GenerateInitializationForMappingStateVar(VariableDeclaration varDecl, Mapping mapping)
688  {
689  BoogieMapSelect lhsMap = CreateDistinctArrayMappingAddress(currentStmtList, varDecl);
690 
691  //nested arrays (only 1 level for now)
692  if (mapping.ValueType is ArrayTypeName array)
693  {
694  Console.WriteLine($"Warning: A mapping with nested array {varDecl.Name} of valuetype {mapping.ValueType.ToString()}");
695 
696  InitializeNestedArrayMappingStateVar(varDecl, mapping);
697  }
698  else if (mapping.ValueType is Mapping mappingNested)
699  {
700  InitializeNestedArrayMappingStateVar(varDecl, mapping);
701  // TODO: add the initialization of m[i][j]
702  }
703  else if (mapping.ValueType is UserDefinedTypeName userTypeName ||
704  mapping.ValueType.ToString().Equals("address") ||
705  mapping.ValueType.ToString().Equals("address payable") ||
706  mapping.ValueType.ToString().StartsWith("bytes")
707  )
708  {
709  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieCommentCmd($"Initialize address/contract mapping {varDecl.Name}"));
710 
711  BoogieType mapKeyType;
712  BoogieMapSelect lhs;
713  GetBoogieTypesFromMapping(varDecl, mapping, out mapKeyType, out lhs);
714  if (!context.TranslateFlags.QuantFreeAllocs)
715  {
716  var qVar = QVarGenerator.NewQVar(0, 0);
717  BoogieExpr zeroExpr = new BoogieIdentifierExpr("null");
718 
719  if (mapping.ValueType.ToString().StartsWith("bytes"))
720  zeroExpr = new BoogieLiteralExpr(BigInteger.Zero);
721 
722  var bodyExpr = new BoogieBinaryOperation(
723  BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.EQ,
724  new BoogieMapSelect(lhs, qVar),
725  zeroExpr);
726  var qExpr = new BoogieQuantifiedExpr(true, new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>() {qVar},
727  new List<BoogieType>() {mapKeyType}, bodyExpr);
728  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssumeCmd(qExpr));
729  }
730  else
731  {
732  if (mapping.ValueType.ToString().StartsWith("bytes"))
733  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs,
734  GetCallExprForZeroInit(mapKeyType, BoogieType.Int)));
735  else
736  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs, GetCallExprForZeroInit(mapKeyType, BoogieType.Ref)));
737  }
738  }
739  else if (mapping.ValueType.ToString().Equals("bool"))
740  {
741  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieCommentCmd($"Initialize Boolean mapping {varDecl.Name}"));
742 
743  BoogieType mapKeyType;
744  BoogieMapSelect lhs;
745  GetBoogieTypesFromMapping(varDecl, mapping, out mapKeyType, out lhs);
746  if (!context.TranslateFlags.QuantFreeAllocs)
747  {
748  var qVar = QVarGenerator.NewQVar(0, 0);
749  var bodyExpr =
750  new BoogieUnaryOperation(BoogieUnaryOperation.Opcode.NOT, new BoogieMapSelect(lhs, qVar));
751  var qExpr = new BoogieQuantifiedExpr(true, new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>() {qVar},
752  new List<BoogieType>() {mapKeyType}, bodyExpr);
753  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssumeCmd(qExpr));
754  }
755  else
756  {
757  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs, GetCallExprForZeroInit(mapKeyType, BoogieType.Bool)));
758  }
759  }
760  // TODO: Cleanup, StartsWith("uint") can include uint[12] as well.
761  else if (mapping.ValueType.ToString().StartsWith("uint") ||
762  mapping.ValueType.ToString().StartsWith("int"))
763  {
764  // Issue a warning for intXX type in case /useModularArithemtic option is used:
765  if (context.TranslateFlags.UseModularArithmetic && mapping.ValueType.ToString().StartsWith("int"))
766  {
767  Console.WriteLine($"Warning: signed integer arithmetic is not handled with /useModularArithmetic option");
768  }
769 
770  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieCommentCmd($"Initialize Integer mapping {varDecl.Name}"));
771 
772  BoogieType mapKeyType;
773  BoogieMapSelect lhs;
774  GetBoogieTypesFromMapping(varDecl, mapping, out mapKeyType, out lhs);
775  if (!context.TranslateFlags.QuantFreeAllocs)
776  {
777  var qVar = QVarGenerator.NewQVar(0, 0);
778  var bodyExpr = new BoogieBinaryOperation(
779  BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.EQ,
780  new BoogieMapSelect(lhs, qVar),
781  new BoogieLiteralExpr(0));
782  var qExpr = new BoogieQuantifiedExpr(true, new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>() {qVar},
783  new List<BoogieType>() {mapKeyType}, bodyExpr);
784  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssumeCmd(qExpr));
785  }
786  else
787  {
788  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs, GetCallExprForZeroInit(mapKeyType, BoogieType.Int)));
789  }
790 
791  if (context.TranslateFlags.InstrumentSums)
792  {
793  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(getSumAccess(lhsMap), new BoogieLiteralExpr(BigInteger.Zero)));
794  }
795  }
796  else
797  {
798  Console.WriteLine($"Warning: A mapping with complex value type {varDecl.Name} of valuetype {mapping.ValueType.ToString()}");
799  }
800  }

802  private void GenerateInitializationForElementaryTypes(VariableDeclaration varDecl, ElementaryTypeName elementaryType)
803  {
804  if (elementaryType.TypeDescriptions.TypeString.Equals("address") || elementaryType.TypeDescriptions.TypeString.Equals("address payable"))
805  {
806  string varName = TransUtils.GetCanonicalStateVariableName(varDecl, context);
807  BoogieExpr lhs = new BoogieMapSelect(new BoogieIdentifierExpr(varName), new BoogieIdentifierExpr("this"));
808  BoogieExpr rhs = new BoogieIdentifierExpr("null");
809  if (varDecl.Value != null)
810  {
811  VeriSolAssert(varDecl.Value is FunctionCall, $"We only support initialization of hte form address x = address(...);, found {varDecl.Value.ToString()}");
812  rhs = TranslateExpr(varDecl.Value);
813  }
814  BoogieAssignCmd assignCmd = new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs, rhs);
815  currentStmtList.AddStatement(assignCmd);
816  }
817  else if (elementaryType.TypeDescriptions.TypeString.Equals("bool"))
818  {
819  string varName = TransUtils.GetCanonicalStateVariableName(varDecl, context);
820  BoogieExpr lhs = new BoogieMapSelect(new BoogieIdentifierExpr(varName), new BoogieIdentifierExpr("this"));
821  bool value = false;
822  if (varDecl.Value != null && varDecl.Value.ToString() == "true")
823  {
824  value = true;
825  }
826  BoogieAssignCmd assignCmd = new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs, new BoogieLiteralExpr(value));
827  currentStmtList.AddStatement(assignCmd);
828  }
829  else if (elementaryType.TypeDescriptions.TypeString.Equals("string"))
830  {
831  string x = "";
832  if (varDecl.Value != null)
833  {
834  x = varDecl.Value.ToString();
835  x = x.Substring(1, x.Length - 2); //to strip off the single quotations
836  }
837  int hashCode = x.GetHashCode();
838  BigInteger num = new BigInteger(hashCode);
839  string varName = TransUtils.GetCanonicalStateVariableName(varDecl, context);
840  BoogieExpr lhs = new BoogieMapSelect(new BoogieIdentifierExpr(varName), new BoogieIdentifierExpr("this"));
841  BoogieAssignCmd assignCmd = new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs, new BoogieLiteralExpr(num));
842  currentStmtList.AddStatement(assignCmd);
843  }
844  else //it is integer valued
845  {
846  // Issue a warning for intXX variables in case /useModularArithemtic option is used:
847  if (context.TranslateFlags.UseModularArithmetic && varDecl.TypeDescriptions.IsInt())
848  {
849  Console.WriteLine($"Warning: signed integer arithmetic is not handled with /useModularArithmetic option");
850  }
851 
852  string varName = TransUtils.GetCanonicalStateVariableName(varDecl, context);
853  BoogieExpr lhs = new BoogieMapSelect(new BoogieIdentifierExpr(varName), new BoogieIdentifierExpr("this"));
854  var bigInt = (BoogieExpr)new BoogieLiteralExpr(BigInteger.Zero);
855  if (varDecl.Value != null)
856  {
857  bigInt = TranslateExpr(varDecl.Value); //TODO: any complex expression will crash
858  }
859  BoogieAssignCmd assignCmd = new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs, bigInt);
860  currentStmtList.AddStatement(assignCmd);
861  }
862  }

864  private void InitializeNestedArrayMappingStateVar(VariableDeclaration varDecl, Mapping mapping)
865  {
866  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieCommentCmd($"Initialize length of 1-level nested array in {varDecl.Name}"));
867  // Issue with inferring Array[] expressions in GetBoogieTypesFromMapping (TODO: use GetBoogieTypesFromMapping after fix)
868  var mapKeyType = MapArrayHelper.InferExprTypeFromTypeString(mapping.KeyType.TypeDescriptions.ToString());
869  string mapName = MapArrayHelper.GetMemoryMapName(mapKeyType, BoogieType.Ref);
870  string varName = TransUtils.GetCanonicalStateVariableName(varDecl, context);
871  var varExpr = new BoogieIdentifierExpr(varName);
872  //lhs is Mem_t_ref[x[this]]
873  var lhs0 = new BoogieMapSelect(new BoogieIdentifierExpr(mapName),
874  new BoogieMapSelect(varExpr, new BoogieIdentifierExpr("this")));
875 
876  var qVar1 = QVarGenerator.NewQVar(0, 0);
877  //lhs is Mem_t_ref[x[this]][i]
878  var lhs1 = new BoogieMapSelect(lhs0, qVar1);
879 
880  if (!context.TranslateFlags.LazyNestedAlloc)
881  {
882  //Length[Mem_t_ref[x[this]][i]] == 0
883  var bodyExpr = new BoogieBinaryOperation(
884  BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.EQ,
885  new BoogieMapSelect(new BoogieIdentifierExpr("Length"), lhs1),
886  new BoogieLiteralExpr(0));
887  var qExpr = new BoogieQuantifiedExpr(true, new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>() {qVar1},
888  new List<BoogieType>() {mapKeyType}, bodyExpr);
889  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssumeCmd(qExpr));
890 
891  //Nested arrays are disjoint and disjoint from other addresses
892  BoogieExpr allocExpr = new BoogieMapSelect(new BoogieIdentifierExpr("Alloc"), lhs1);
893  var negAllocExpr = new BoogieUnaryOperation(BoogieUnaryOperation.Opcode.NOT, allocExpr);
894  var negAllocQExpr = new BoogieQuantifiedExpr(true, new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>() {qVar1},
895  new List<BoogieType>() {mapKeyType}, negAllocExpr);
896  //assume forall i !Alloc[M_t_ref[x[this]][i]]
897  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssumeCmd(negAllocQExpr));
898  //call HavocAllocMany()
899  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieCallCmd("HavocAllocMany", new List<BoogieExpr>(),
900  new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>()));
901  //assume forall i. Alloc[M_t_ref[x[this]][i]]
902  var allocQExpr = new BoogieQuantifiedExpr(true, new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>() {qVar1},
903  new List<BoogieType>() {mapKeyType}, allocExpr);
904  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssumeCmd(allocQExpr));
905 
906  //Two different keys/indices within the same array are distinct
907  //forall i, j: i != j ==> M_t_ref[x[this]][i] != M_t_ref[x[this]][j]
908  var qVar2 = QVarGenerator.NewQVar(0, 1);
909  var lhs2 = new BoogieMapSelect(lhs0, qVar2);
910  var distinctQVars = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.EQ, qVar1, qVar2);
911  var distinctLhs = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.NEQ, lhs1, lhs2);
912  var triggers = new List<BoogieExpr>() {lhs1, lhs2};
913 
914  var neqExpr = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.OR, distinctQVars, distinctLhs);
915  var distinctQExpr = new BoogieQuantifiedExpr(true, new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>() {qVar1, qVar2},
916  new List<BoogieType>() {mapKeyType, mapKeyType}, neqExpr, triggers);
917  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssumeCmd(distinctQExpr));
918  }
919  else
920  {
921  if (context.TranslateFlags.QuantFreeAllocs)
922  {
923  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs0, GetCallExprForZeroInit(mapKeyType, BoogieType.Ref)));
924  }
925  else
926  {
927  var bodyExpr = new BoogieBinaryOperation(
928  BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.EQ,
929  lhs1,
930  new BoogieIdentifierExpr("null"));
931  var qExpr = new BoogieQuantifiedExpr(true, new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>() {qVar1},
932  new List<BoogieType>() {mapKeyType}, bodyExpr);
933  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssumeCmd(qExpr));
934  }
935  }
936  }

960  private void GetBoogieTypesFromMapping(VariableDeclaration varDecl, Mapping mapping, out BoogieType mapKeyType, out BoogieMapSelect lhs)
961  {
962  mapKeyType = MapArrayHelper.InferExprTypeFromTypeString(mapping.KeyType.TypeDescriptions.ToString());

973  new BoogieMapSelect(varExpr, new BoogieIdentifierExpr("this")));

976  // generate the default empty constructors, including an internal one without base ctors, and an actual one with base ctors
977  // TODO: refactor this code with the code to generate constructor code when definition is present
978  private void GenerateDefaultConstructor(ContractDefinition contract)
979  {
980  // generate the internal one without base constructors
981  string procName = contract.Name + "_" + contract.Name + "_NoBaseCtor";
982  currentBoogieProc = procName;
983  if (!boogieToLocalVarsMap.ContainsKey(currentBoogieProc))
984  {
985  boogieToLocalVarsMap[currentBoogieProc] = new List<BoogieVariable>();
986  }
987 
988  List<BoogieVariable> inParams = TransUtils.GetDefaultInParams();
989  List<BoogieVariable> outParams = new List<BoogieVariable>();
990  List<BoogieAttribute> attributes = new List<BoogieAttribute>();
991  if (context.TranslateFlags.GenerateInlineAttributes)
992  {
993  attributes.Add(new BoogieAttribute("inline", 1));
994  };
995  BoogieProcedure procedure = new BoogieProcedure(procName, inParams, outParams, attributes);
996  context.Program.AddDeclaration(procedure);
997 
998  BoogieStmtList procBody = GenerateInitializationStmts(contract);
999  List<BoogieVariable> localVars = boogieToLocalVarsMap[currentBoogieProc];
1000  BoogieImplementation implementation = new BoogieImplementation(procName, inParams, outParams, localVars, procBody);
1001  context.Program.AddDeclaration(implementation);
1002 
1003  // generate the actual one with base constructors
1004  string ctorName = contract.Name + "_" + contract.Name;
1005  BoogieProcedure ctorWithBaseCalls = new BoogieProcedure(ctorName, inParams, outParams, attributes);
1006  context.Program.AddDeclaration(ctorWithBaseCalls);
1007 
1008  List<BoogieVariable> ctorLocalVars = new List<BoogieVariable>();
1009  BoogieStmtList ctorBody = new BoogieStmtList();
1010 
1011  // add the printing for argument
1012  // Print function argument values to corral.txt for counterexample:
1013  PrintArguments(null, inParams, ctorBody);
1014 
1015  // print sourcefile, and line of the contract start for
1016  // forcing Corral to print values consistently
1017  if (!context.TranslateFlags.NoSourceLineInfoFlag)
1018  ctorBody.AddStatement(InstrumentSourceFileAndLineInfo(contract));
1019 
1020  List<int> baseContractIds = new List<int>(contract.LinearizedBaseContracts);
1021  baseContractIds.Reverse();
1022  foreach (int id in baseContractIds)
1023  {
1024  ContractDefinition baseContract = context.GetASTNodeById(id) as ContractDefinition;
1025  VeriSolAssert(baseContract != null);
1026 
1027  string callee = TransUtils.GetCanonicalConstructorName(baseContract);
1028  if (baseContract.Name == contract.Name)
1029  {
1030  // for current contract, call the body that does not have the base calls
1031  // for base contracts, call the wrapper constructor
1032  callee += "_NoBaseCtor";
1033  }
1034 
1035  List<BoogieExpr> inputs = new List<BoogieExpr>();
1036  List<BoogieIdentifierExpr> outputs = new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>();
1037 
1038  InheritanceSpecifier inheritanceSpecifier = GetInheritanceSpecifieWithArgsOfBase(contract, baseContract);
1039  if (inheritanceSpecifier != null)
1040  {
1041  inputs.Add(new BoogieIdentifierExpr("this"));
1042  inputs.Add(new BoogieIdentifierExpr("msgsender_MSG"));
1043  inputs.Add(new BoogieIdentifierExpr("msgvalue_MSG"));
1044  foreach (Expression argument in inheritanceSpecifier.Arguments)
1045  {
1046  inputs.Add(TranslateExpr(argument));
1047  }
1048  }
1049  else // no argument for this base constructor
1050  {
1051 
1052  if (baseContract.Name == contract.Name)
1053  {
1054  // only do this for the derived contract
1055  foreach (BoogieVariable param in inParams)
1056  {
1057  inputs.Add(new BoogieIdentifierExpr(param.TypedIdent.Name));
1058  }
1059  }
1060  else
1061  {
1062  // Do we call the constructor or assume that it is invoked in teh base contract?
1063  // since it needs argument, we cannot invoke it here (Issue #101)
1064  var baseCtr = context.IsConstructorDefined(baseContract) ? context.GetConstructorByContract(baseContract) : null;
1065  if (baseCtr != null && baseCtr.Parameters.Length() > 0)
1066  {
1067  continue;
1068  } else if (!currentContract.BaseContracts.Any(x => x.BaseName.Name.Equals(baseContract.Name)))
1069  {
1070  Console.WriteLine($"Warning!!: Invoking base constructor { callee} that is not explicitly in inheritance list of {currentContract.Name}...");
1071  }
1072  inputs.Add(new BoogieIdentifierExpr("this"));
1073  inputs.Add(new BoogieIdentifierExpr("msgsender_MSG"));
1074  inputs.Add(new BoogieIdentifierExpr("msgvalue_MSG"));
1075  }
1076  }
1077  BoogieCallCmd callCmd = new BoogieCallCmd(callee, inputs, outputs);
1078  ctorBody.AddStatement(callCmd);
1079  }
1080  BoogieImplementation ctorImpl = new BoogieImplementation(ctorName, inParams, outParams, ctorLocalVars, ctorBody);
1081  context.Program.AddDeclaration(ctorImpl);
1082  }
1083 
1084  // generate actual constructor procedures that invoke constructors without base in linearized order
1085  private void GenerateConstructorWithBaseCalls(FunctionDefinition ctor, List<BoogieVariable> inParams)
1086  {
1087  VeriSolAssert(ctor.IsConstructor, $"{ctor.Name} is not a constructor");
1088 
1089  ContractDefinition contract = context.GetContractByFunction(ctor);
1090  string procName = contract.Name + "_" + contract.Name;
1091 
1092  // no output params for constructor
1093  List<BoogieVariable> outParams = new List<BoogieVariable>();
1094  List<BoogieAttribute> attributes = new List<BoogieAttribute>()
1095  {
1096  new BoogieAttribute("constructor"),
1097  new BoogieAttribute("public"),
1098  };
1099  if (context.TranslateFlags.GenerateInlineAttributes)
1100  {
1101  attributes.Add(new BoogieAttribute("inline", 1));
1102  };
1103  BoogieProcedure procedure = new BoogieProcedure(procName, inParams, outParams, attributes);
1104  context.Program.AddDeclaration(procedure);
1105 
1106  // skip if it in ignored set
1107  if (context.IsMethodInIgnoredSet(ctor, currentContract))
1108  {
1109  Console.WriteLine($"Warning!: Ignoring constructor {ctor.Name} in contract {currentContract.Name} specified using /ignoreMethod:");
1110  }
1111  else
1112  {
1113  // no local variables for constructor
1114  List<BoogieVariable> localVars = new List<BoogieVariable>();
1115  BoogieStmtList ctorBody = new BoogieStmtList();
1116 
1117  List<int> baseContractIds = new List<int>(contract.LinearizedBaseContracts);
1118  baseContractIds.Reverse();
1119 
1120  // Print function argument values to corral.txt for counterexample:
1121  PrintArguments(ctor, inParams, ctorBody);
1122 
1123  //Note that the current derived contract appears as a baseContractId
1124  foreach (int id in baseContractIds)
1125  {
1126  ContractDefinition baseContract = context.GetASTNodeById(id) as ContractDefinition;
1127  VeriSolAssert(baseContract != null);
1128 
1129  // since we are not translating any statements, currentStmtList remains null
1130  currentStmtList = new BoogieStmtList();
1131

1159  foreach (Expression argument in modifierInvocation.Arguments)

1162  }
1163  }

1170  {

1172  }
1173  }

1176  // Do we call the constructor or assume that it is invoked in teh base contract?
1177  // Do we call the constructor or assume that it is invoked in teh base contract?

1346  public override bool Visit(VariableDeclarationStatement node)
1347  {
1348  preTranslationAction(node);
1349  foreach (VariableDeclaration varDecl in node.Declarations)
1350  {
1351  string name = TransUtils.GetCanonicalLocalVariableName(varDecl, context);
1352  BoogieType type = TransUtils.GetBoogieTypeFromSolidityTypeName(varDecl.TypeName);
1353  // Issue a warning for intXX variables in case /useModularArithemtic option is used:
1354  if (context.TranslateFlags.UseModularArithmetic && varDecl.TypeDescriptions.IsInt())
1355  {
1356  Console.WriteLine($"Warning: signed integer arithmetic is not handled with /useModularArithmetic option");
1357  }
1358  var boogieVariable = new BoogieLocalVariable(new BoogieTypedIdent(name, type));
1359  boogieToLocalVarsMap[currentBoogieProc].Add(boogieVariable);
1360  }
1361 
1362  // handle the initial value of variable declaration
1363  if (node.InitialValue != null)
1364  {
1365  VeriSolAssert(node.Declarations.Count == 1, "Invalid multiple variable declarations");
1366 
1367  // de-sugar to variable declaration and an assignment
1368  VariableDeclaration varDecl = node.Declarations[0];
1369 
1370  Identifier identifier = new Identifier();
1371  identifier.Name = varDecl.Name;
1372  identifier.ReferencedDeclaration = varDecl.Id;
1373  identifier.TypeDescriptions = varDecl.TypeDescriptions;
1374 
1375  Assignment assignment = new Assignment();
1376  assignment.LeftHandSide = identifier;
1377  assignment.Operator = "=";
1378  assignment.RightHandSide = node.InitialValue;
1379 
1380  // call the visitor for assignments
1381  assignment.Accept(this);
1382  }
1383  else
1384  {
1385  // havoc the declared variables
1386  List<BoogieIdentifierExpr> varsToHavoc = new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>();
1387  foreach (VariableDeclaration varDecl in node.Declarations)
1388  {
1389  string varIdent = TransUtils.GetCanonicalLocalVariableName(varDecl, context);
1390  varsToHavoc.Add(new BoogieIdentifierExpr(varIdent));
1391  }
1392  BoogieHavocCmd havocCmd = new BoogieHavocCmd(varsToHavoc);
1393  currentStmtList.AppendStmtList(BoogieStmtList.MakeSingletonStmtList(havocCmd));
1394  }
1395  return false;
1396  }

1424  private BoogieExpr AddModuloOp(Expression srcExpr, BoogieExpr expr, TypeDescription type)

1456  public override bool Visit(Assignment node)
1457  {
1458  preTranslationAction(node);
1459  List<BoogieExpr> lhs = new List<BoogieExpr>();
1460  List<BoogieType> lhsTypes = new List<BoogieType>(); //stores types in case of tuples
1461  List<Expression> lhsExprs;
1462 
1463  bool isTupleAssignment = false;
1464 
1465  if (node.LeftHandSide is TupleExpression tuple)
1466  {
1467  // we only handle the case (e1, e2, .., _, _) = funcCall(...)
1468  lhs.AddRange(tuple.Components.ConvertAll(x => TranslateExpr(x)));
1469  isTupleAssignment = true;
1470  lhsTypes.AddRange(tuple.Components.ConvertAll(x => MapArrayHelper.InferExprTypeFromTypeString(x.TypeDescriptions.TypeString)));
1471  lhsExprs = tuple.Components;
1472  }
1473  else
1474  {
1475  lhs.Add(TranslateExpr(node.LeftHandSide));
1476  lhsExprs = new List<Expression>();
1477  lhsExprs.Add(node.LeftHandSide);
1478  }
1479 
1480  // TODO: this part should go into Translate a function call expression
1481  if (node.RightHandSide is FunctionCall funcCall)
1482  {
1483  // if lhs is not an identifier (e.g. a[i]), then
1484  // we have to introduce a temporary
1485  // we do it even when lhs is identifier to keep translation simple
1486  var tmpVars = new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>();
1487 
1488  var oldStmtList = currentStmtList;
1489  currentStmtList = new BoogieStmtList();
1490 
1491  if (!isTupleAssignment) {
1492  tmpVars.Add(lhs[0] is BoogieIdentifierExpr ? lhs[0] as BoogieIdentifierExpr : MkNewLocalVariableForFunctionReturn(funcCall));
1493  } else {
1494  // always use temporaries for tuples regardless if lhs[i] is an identifier
1495  tmpVars.AddRange(lhsTypes.ConvertAll(x => MkNewLocalVariableWithType(x)));
1496  }
1497 
1498  var tmpVariableAssumes = currentStmtList;
1499  currentStmtList = oldStmtList;
1500 
1501  // a Boolean to decide is we needed to use tmpVar
1502  bool usedTmpVar = true;
1503 
1504  if (IsContractConstructor(funcCall))
1505  {
1506  VeriSolAssert(!isTupleAssignment, "Not expecting a tuple for Constructors");
1507  TranslateNewStatement(funcCall, tmpVars[0]);
1508  }
1509  else if (IsStructConstructor(funcCall))
1510  {
1511  VeriSolAssert(!isTupleAssignment, "Not expecting a tuple for Constructors");
1512  TranslateStructConstructor(funcCall, tmpVars[0]);
1513  }
1514  else if (IsKeccakFunc(funcCall))
1515  {
1516  VeriSolAssert(!isTupleAssignment, "Not expecting a tuple for Keccak256");
1517  TranslateKeccakFuncCall(funcCall, lhs[0]); //this is not a procedure call in Boogie
1518  usedTmpVar = false;
1519  }
1520  else if (IsAbiEncodePackedFunc(funcCall))
1521  {
1522  TranslateAbiEncodedFuncCall(funcCall, tmpVars[0]); //this is not a procedure call in Boogie
1523  VeriSolAssert(!isTupleAssignment, "Not expecting a tuple for abi.encodePacked");
1524  usedTmpVar = false;
1525  }
1526  else if (IsTypeCast(funcCall))
1527  {
1528  // assume the type cast is used as: obj = C(var);
1529  VeriSolAssert(!isTupleAssignment, "Not expecting a tuple for type cast");
1530  bool isElementaryCast; //not used at this site
1531  TranslateTypeCast(funcCall, tmpVars[0], out isElementaryCast); //this is not a procedure call in Boogie
1532  usedTmpVar = false;
1533  }
1534  else // normal function calls
1535  {
1536  VeriSolAssert(tmpVars is List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>, $"tmpVar has to be a list of Boogie identifiers: {tmpVars}");
1537  TranslateFunctionCalls(funcCall, tmpVars);
1538  }
1539  if (context.TranslateFlags.InstrumentSums)
1540  {
1541  updateAssignedSums(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.SUB, lhsExprs, lhs);
1542  }
1543  if (!isTupleAssignment)
1544  {
1545  if (usedTmpVar || !(lhs[0] is BoogieIdentifierExpr)) //bad bug: was && before!!
1546  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs[0], tmpVars[0]));
1547  } else
1548  {
1549  for (int i = 0; i < lhs.Count; ++i)
1550  {
1551  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs[i], tmpVars[i]));
1552  }
1553  }
1554  if (context.TranslateFlags.InstrumentSums)
1555  {
1556  updateAssignedSums(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.ADD, lhsExprs, lhs);
1557  }
1558  foreach(var block in tmpVariableAssumes.BigBlocks)
1559  {
1560  foreach(var stmt in block.SimpleCmds)
1561  currentStmtList.AddStatement(stmt);
1562 
1563  }
1564  }
1565  else
1566  {
1567  if (isTupleAssignment)
1568  VeriSolAssert(false, "Not implemented...currently only support assignment of tuples as returns of a function call");
1569 
1570  BoogieExpr rhs = TranslateExpr(node.RightHandSide);
1571  BoogieStmtList stmtList = new BoogieStmtList();
1572  BoogieExpr assignedExpr = new BoogieExpr();
1573  switch (node.Operator)
1574  {
1575  case "=":
1576  stmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs[0], rhs));
1577  break;
1578  case "+=":
1579  assignedExpr = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.ADD, lhs[0], rhs);
1580  assignedExpr = AddModuloOp(node.LeftHandSide, assignedExpr, node.LeftHandSide.TypeDescriptions);
1581  stmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs[0], assignedExpr));
1582  break;
1583  case "-=":
1584  assignedExpr = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.SUB, lhs[0], rhs);
1585  assignedExpr = AddModuloOp(node.LeftHandSide, assignedExpr, node.LeftHandSide.TypeDescriptions);
1586  stmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs[0], assignedExpr));
1587  break;
1588  case "*=":
1589  assignedExpr = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.MUL, lhs[0], rhs);
1590  assignedExpr = AddModuloOp(node.LeftHandSide, assignedExpr, node.LeftHandSide.TypeDescriptions);
1591  stmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs[0], assignedExpr));
1592  break;
1593  case "/=":
1594  assignedExpr = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.DIV, lhs[0], rhs);
1595  assignedExpr = AddModuloOp(node.LeftHandSide, assignedExpr, node.LeftHandSide.TypeDescriptions);
1596  stmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs[0], assignedExpr));
1597  break;
1598  default:
1599  VeriSolAssert(false, $"Unknown assignment operator: {node.Operator}");
1600  break;
1601  }
1602 
1603  if (context.TranslateFlags.InstrumentSums)
1604  {
1605  updateAssignedSums(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.SUB, lhsExprs, lhs);
1606  }
1607  currentStmtList.AppendStmtList(stmtList);
1608  if (context.TranslateFlags.InstrumentSums)
1609  {
1610  updateAssignedSums(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.ADD, lhsExprs, lhs);
1611  }
1612  }
1613 
1614  var lhsType = node.LeftHandSide.TypeDescriptions != null ?
1615  node.LeftHandSide.TypeDescriptions :
1616  (node.RightHandSide.TypeDescriptions != null ?
1617  node.RightHandSide.TypeDescriptions : null);
1618 
1619  if (lhsType != null && !isTupleAssignment)
1620  {
1621  var callCmd = InstrumentForPrintingData(lhsType, lhs[0], node.LeftHandSide.ToString());
1622  if (callCmd != null)
1623  {
1624  currentStmtList.AddStatement(callCmd);
1625  }
1626  }
1627 
1628  return false;
1629  }

1648  public override bool Visit(Return node)
1649  {
1650  preTranslationAction(node);
1651  if (node.Expression == null)
1652  {
1653  //Void
1654  BoogieReturnCmd returnCmd = new BoogieReturnCmd();
1655  if (currentPostlude == null)
1656  {
1657  currentStmtList.AppendStmtList(BoogieStmtList.MakeSingletonStmtList(returnCmd));
1658  }
1659  else
1660  {
1661  currentStmtList.AppendStmtList(currentPostlude);
1662  currentStmtList.AddStatement(returnCmd);
1663  }
1664  }
1665  else
1666  {
1667  BoogieExpr retExpr = TranslateExpr(node.Expression); //TODO: handle tuples here?
1668  var retParamCount = 0;
1669  if (node.Expression is TupleExpression tuple)
1670  {
1671  //Tuple
1672  if (!(retExpr is BoogieTupleExpr))
1673  {
1674  VeriSolAssert(false, "Expecting a Boogie tuple expression here");
1675  }
1676  var bTupleExpr = retExpr as BoogieTupleExpr;
1677 
1678  //turn the tuple assignment into a serial assignment [TODO: understand the evaluation semantics]
1679  foreach (var retVarDecl in currentFunction.ReturnParameters.Parameters)
1680  {
1681  string retVarName = String.IsNullOrEmpty(retVarDecl.Name) ?
1682  $"__ret_{retParamCount}_" :
1683  TransUtils.GetCanonicalLocalVariableName(retVarDecl, context);
1684  BoogieIdentifierExpr retVar = new BoogieIdentifierExpr(retVarName);
1685  BoogieAssignCmd assignCmd = new BoogieAssignCmd(retVar, bTupleExpr.Arguments[retParamCount++]);
1686  currentStmtList.AppendStmtList(BoogieStmtList.MakeSingletonStmtList(assignCmd)); //TODO: simultaneous updates
1687  }
1688  }
1689  else
1690  {
1691  //Singleton
1692  var retVarDecl = currentFunction.ReturnParameters.Parameters[0];
1693  string retVarName = String.IsNullOrEmpty(retVarDecl.Name) ?
1694  $"__ret_{retParamCount++}_" :
1695  TransUtils.GetCanonicalLocalVariableName(retVarDecl, context);
1696  BoogieIdentifierExpr retVar = new BoogieIdentifierExpr(retVarName);
1697  BoogieAssignCmd assignCmd = new BoogieAssignCmd(retVar, retExpr);
1698  currentStmtList.AppendStmtList(BoogieStmtList.MakeSingletonStmtList(assignCmd)); //TODO: simultaneous updates
1699  }
1700 
1701  if (currentPostlude != null)
1702  {
1703  currentStmtList.AppendStmtList(currentPostlude);
1704  }
1705  // add a return command, in case the original return expr is in the middle of the function body
1706  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieReturnCmd());
1707  }

1711  private void AddAssumeForUints(Expression expr, BoogieExpr boogieExpr, TypeDescription typeDesc)
1712  {
1713  // skip based on a flag
1714  if (context.TranslateFlags.NoUnsignedAssumesFlag)
1715  return;
1716 
1717  // Add positive number assume for uints
1718  if (typeDesc!=null && typeDesc.IsUint())
1719  {
1720  var ge0 = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.GE, boogieExpr, new BoogieLiteralExpr(BigInteger.Zero));
1721 
1722  if (context.TranslateFlags.UseModularArithmetic)
1723  {
1724  var isUint = typeDesc.IsUintWSize(expr, out uint sz);
1725  if (isUint)
1726  {
1727  VeriSolAssert(sz != 0, $"size of uint lhs is zero");
1728  BigInteger maxUIntValue = (BigInteger)Math.Pow(2, sz);
1729  var tmp = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.LT, boogieExpr, new BoogieLiteralExpr(maxUIntValue));
1730  ge0 = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.AND, ge0, tmp);
1731  }
1732  }
1733 
1734 
1735  var assumePositiveCmd = new BoogieAssumeCmd(ge0);
1736  currentStmtList.AppendStmtList(BoogieStmtList.MakeSingletonStmtList(assumePositiveCmd));
1737  }
1738  }

1831  /// <summary>
1832  ///
1833  /// </summary>
1834  /// <param name="specStringCall">"Invariant_VeriSol", "Ensures_VeriSol", "Requires_VeriSol"</param>
1835  /// <param name="body"></param>
1836  /// <param name="bodyWithoutSpecNodes"></param>
1837  /// <returns></returns>
1838  private List<BoogieExpr> ExtractSpecifications(string specStringCall, BoogieStmtList body, out BoogieStmtList bodyWithoutSpecNodes)
1839  {
1840  bodyWithoutSpecNodes = new BoogieStmtList();
1841  List<BoogieExpr> specArguments = new List<BoogieExpr>();
1842  foreach (var bigBlock in body.BigBlocks)
1843  {
1844  foreach (var stmt in bigBlock.SimpleCmds)
1845  {
1846  var callCmd = stmt as BoogieCallCmd;
1847  if (callCmd == null)
1848  {
1849  bodyWithoutSpecNodes.AddStatement(stmt);
1850  continue;
1851  }
1852  if (callCmd.Callee.Equals(specStringCall))
1853  {
1854  //first 3 args are {this, msg.sender, msg.value}
1855  if (specStringCall.Equals("Modifies_VeriSol"))
1856  {
1857  VeriSolAssert(callCmd.Ins.Count == 5, $"For Modifies clause, found {specStringCall}(..) with unexpected number of args (expected 5)");
1858  specArguments.Add(TranslateModifiesStmt(callCmd.Ins[3], callCmd.Ins[4]));
1859  }
1860  else
1861  {
1862  VeriSolAssert(callCmd.Ins.Count == 4, $"Found {specStringCall}(..) with unexpected number of args (expected 4)");
1863  specArguments.Add(callCmd.Ins[3]);
1864  }
1865  } else
1866  {
1867  bodyWithoutSpecNodes.AddStatement(stmt);
1868  }
1869  }
1870  }
1871  return specArguments;
1872  }

1874  private BoogieExpr TranslateModifiesStmt(BoogieExpr boogieExpr1, BoogieExpr boogieExpr2)
1875  {
1876  //has to be M_ref_int[mapp[this]] instead of mapp[this]
1877  var mapName = MapArrayHelper.GetMemoryMapName(BoogieType.Ref, BoogieType.Int);
1878  var mappingExpr = new BoogieMapSelect(new BoogieIdentifierExpr(mapName), boogieExpr1);
1879 
1880  //boogieExpr2 is a tuple, we need to flatten it into an array
1881  var boogieTupleExpr = boogieExpr2 as BoogieTupleExpr;
1882  VeriSolAssert(boogieTupleExpr != null, $"Expecting tuple expression, found {boogieExpr2.ToString()}");
1883  VeriSolAssert(boogieTupleExpr.Arguments.Count > 0, $"Expecting non-tuple expression, found {boogieExpr2.ToString()}");
1884  VeriSolAssert(boogieTupleExpr.Arguments.Count < 10, $"Expecting tuple expression of size < 10, found {boogieExpr2.ToString()}");
1885 
1886  // forall x: Ref :: x == m1 || x == m2 ... || x == mi || map[x] == old(map[x])
1887  var qVar1 = QVarGenerator.NewQVar(0, 0);
1888  var bodyExpr = (BoogieExpr)new BoogieLiteralExpr(false);
1889  for (int i = 0; i < boogieTupleExpr.Arguments.Count; i++)
1890  {
1891  bodyExpr =
1892  new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.OR, bodyExpr,
1893  (new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.EQ, qVar1, boogieTupleExpr.Arguments[i])));
1894  }
1895  var mapExpr = new BoogieMapSelect(mappingExpr, (BoogieExpr)qVar1);
1896  var oldMapExpr = new BoogieFuncCallExpr("old", new List<BoogieExpr>() { mapExpr });
1897  var eqExpr = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.EQ, mapExpr, oldMapExpr);
1898  bodyExpr = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.OR, bodyExpr, eqExpr);
1899  var qBodyExpr = new BoogieQuantifiedExpr(true,
1900  new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>() { qVar1 },
1901  new List<BoogieType>() { BoogieType.Ref },
1902  bodyExpr
1903  );
1904  return qBodyExpr;
1905  }

1969  public override bool Visit(ExpressionStatement node)
1970  {
1971  preTranslationAction(node);
1972  if (node.Expression is UnaryOperation unaryOperation)
1973  {
1974  // only handle increment and decrement operators in a separate statement
1975  VeriSolAssert(!(unaryOperation.SubExpression is UnaryOperation));
1976 
1977  BoogieExpr lhs = TranslateExpr(unaryOperation.SubExpression);
1978  if (unaryOperation.Operator.Equals("++") ||
1979  unaryOperation.Operator.Equals("--"))
1980  {
1981  var oper = unaryOperation.Operator.Equals("++") ? BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.ADD : BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.SUB;
1982  BoogieExpr rhs = new BoogieBinaryOperation(oper, lhs, new BoogieLiteralExpr(1));
1983  rhs = AddModuloOp(unaryOperation.SubExpression, rhs, unaryOperation.SubExpression.TypeDescriptions);
1984  BoogieAssignCmd assignCmd = new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs, rhs);
1985  currentStmtList.AddStatement(assignCmd);
1986 
1987  var typeDescription = unaryOperation.SubExpression.TypeDescriptions;
1988  var isInt = typeDescription.IsInt() || typeDescription.IsUint();
1989  if (context.TranslateFlags.InstrumentSums && isInt && unaryOperation.SubExpression is IndexAccess access &&
1990  lhs is BoogieMapSelect sel && sel.BaseExpr is BoogieMapSelect arrIdent)
1991  {
1992  currentStmtList.AddStatement(adjustSum(oper, arrIdent.Arguments[0], new BoogieLiteralExpr(BigInteger.One)));
1993  }
1994 
1995  //print the value
1996  if (!context.TranslateFlags.NoDataValuesInfoFlag)
1997  {
1998  var callCmd = new BoogieCallCmd("boogie_si_record_sol2Bpl_int", new List<BoogieExpr>() { lhs }, new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>());
1999  callCmd.Attributes = new List<BoogieAttribute>();
2000  callCmd.Attributes.Add(new BoogieAttribute("cexpr", $"\"{unaryOperation.SubExpression.ToString()}\""));
2001  currentStmtList.AddStatement(callCmd);
2002  }
2003  AddAssumeForUints(unaryOperation, lhs, unaryOperation.TypeDescriptions);
2004  }
2005  else if (unaryOperation.Operator.Equals("delete"))
2006  {
2007  var typeDescription = unaryOperation.SubExpression.TypeDescriptions;
2008  var isBasicType = typeDescription.IsInt() || typeDescription.IsUint()
2009  || typeDescription.IsBool() || typeDescription.IsString();
2010 
2011  // var isArrayAccess = unaryOperation.SubExpression is IndexAccess;
2012  if (typeDescription.IsDynamicArray())
2013  {
2014  BoogieExpr element = TranslateExpr(unaryOperation.SubExpression);
2015  BoogieExpr lengthMapSelect = new BoogieMapSelect(new BoogieIdentifierExpr("Length"), element);
2016  BoogieExpr rhs = new BoogieLiteralExpr(BigInteger.Zero);
2017  var assignCmd = new BoogieAssignCmd(lengthMapSelect, rhs);
2018  currentStmtList.AddStatement(assignCmd);
2019 
2020  var isInt = typeDescription.IsInt() || typeDescription.IsUint();
2021  if (context.TranslateFlags.InstrumentSums && isInt)
2022  {
2023  BoogieExpr sumExpr = getSumAccess(element);
2024  var sumAssign = new BoogieAssignCmd(sumExpr, new BoogieLiteralExpr(BigInteger.Zero));
2025  currentStmtList.AddStatement(sumAssign);
2026  }
2027  }
2028  else if (typeDescription.IsStaticArray())
2029  {
2030  // TODO: Handle static arrauy
2031  Console.WriteLine($"Warning!!: Currently not handling delete of static arrays");
2032  }
2033  // This handle cases like delete x with "x" a basic type or delete x[i] when x[i] being a basic type;
2034  else if (isBasicType)
2035  {
2036  var isInt = typeDescription.IsInt() || typeDescription.IsUint();
2037  if (context.TranslateFlags.InstrumentSums && isInt && unaryOperation.SubExpression is IndexAccess access &&
2038  lhs is BoogieMapSelect sel && sel.BaseExpr is BoogieMapSelect arrIdent)
2039  {
2040  currentStmtList.AddStatement(adjustSum(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.SUB, arrIdent.Arguments[0], lhs));
2041  }
2042 
2043  BoogieExpr rhs = null;
2044  if (typeDescription.IsInt() || typeDescription.IsUint())
2045  rhs = new BoogieLiteralExpr(BigInteger.Zero);
2046  else if (typeDescription.IsBool())
2047  rhs = new BoogieLiteralExpr(false);
2048  else if (typeDescription.IsString())
2049  {
2050  var emptyStr = "";
2051  rhs = new BoogieLiteralExpr(new BigInteger(emptyStr.GetHashCode()));
2052  }
2053  var assignCmd = new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs, rhs);
2054  currentStmtList.AddStatement(assignCmd);
2055  }
2056  else
2057  {
2058  Console.WriteLine($"Warning!!: Only handle delete for scalars and arrays, found {typeDescription.TypeString}");
2059  }
2060  }
2061  return false;
2062  }
2063  else
2064  {
2065  // distribute to different visit functions
2066  return true;
2067  }
2068  }

2075  private BoogieExpr TranslateExpr(Expression expr)
2076  {
2077  currentExpr = null;
2078  if (expr is FunctionCall && IsTypeCast((FunctionCall) expr))
2079  {
2080  expr.Accept(this);
2081  VeriSolAssert(currentExpr != null);
2082  }
2083  else if(expr is TupleExpression tuple)
2084  {
2085  var transArgs = new List<BoogieExpr>();
2086  foreach(var e in tuple.Components)
2087  {
2088  e.Accept(this);
2089  VeriSolAssert(currentExpr != null);
2090  transArgs.Add(currentExpr);
2091  }
2092  currentExpr = new BoogieTupleExpr(transArgs);
2093  }
2094  else
2095  {
2096  expr.Accept(this);
2097  VeriSolAssert(currentExpr != null);
2098  }
2099 
2100  // TODO: Many times the type is unknown...
2101  if(expr.TypeDescriptions!=null) // && currentExpr is BoogieIdentifierExpr)
2102  {
2103  AddAssumeForUints(expr, currentExpr, expr.TypeDescriptions);
2104  }
2105 
2106  return currentExpr;
2107  }

2327  var mapSelect = new BoogieMapSelect(new BoogieIdentifierExpr("Length"), indexExpr);
2328  return mapSelect;
2329  }
2330 
2331  public override bool Visit(FunctionCall node)
2332  {
2333  preTranslationAction(node);
2334 
2335  // VeriSolAssert(!(node.Expression is NewExpression), $"new expressions should be handled in assignment");
2336  if (node.Expression is NewExpression)
2337  {
2338  BoogieIdentifierExpr tmpVarExpr = MkNewLocalVariableForFunctionReturn(node);
2339  TranslateNewStatement(node, tmpVarExpr);
2340  currentExpr = tmpVarExpr;
2341  return false;
2342  }
2343 
2344  var functionName = TransUtils.GetFuncNameFromFuncCall(node);
2345 
2346  if (functionName.Equals("assert"))
2347  {
2348  // TODO:
2349  //countNestedFuncCallsRelExprs--;
2350  VeriSolAssert(node.Arguments.Count == 1);
2351  BoogieExpr predicate = TranslateExpr(node.Arguments[0]);
2352  BoogieAssertCmd assertCmd = new BoogieAssertCmd(predicate);
2353  currentStmtList.AddStatement(assertCmd);
2354  }
2355  else if (functionName.Equals("require"))
2356  {
2357  // TODO:
2358  //countNestedFuncCallsRelExprs--;
2359  VeriSolAssert(node.Arguments.Count == 1 || node.Arguments.Count == 2);
2360  BoogieExpr predicate = TranslateExpr(node.Arguments[0]);
2361 
2362  if (!context.TranslateFlags.ModelReverts)
2363  {
2364  BoogieAssumeCmd assumeCmd = new BoogieAssumeCmd(predicate);
2365  currentStmtList.AddStatement(assumeCmd);
2366  }
2367  else
2368  {
2369  BoogieStmtList revertLogic = new BoogieStmtList();
2370 
2371  emitRevertLogic(revertLogic);
2372 
2373  BoogieIfCmd requierCheck = new BoogieIfCmd(new BoogieUnaryOperation(BoogieUnaryOperation.Opcode.NOT, predicate), revertLogic, null);
2374 
2375  currentStmtList.AddStatement(requierCheck);
2376  }
2377  }
2378  else if (functionName.Equals("revert"))
2379  {
2380  VeriSolAssert(node.Arguments.Count == 0 || node.Arguments.Count == 1);
2381  if (!context.TranslateFlags.ModelReverts)
2382  {
2383  BoogieAssumeCmd assumeCmd = new BoogieAssumeCmd(new BoogieLiteralExpr(false));
2384  currentStmtList.AddStatement(assumeCmd);
2385  }
2386  else
2387  {
2388  emitRevertLogic(currentStmtList);
2389  }
2390  }
2391  else if (IsImplicitFunc(node))
2392  {
2393  BoogieIdentifierExpr tmpVarExpr = MkNewLocalVariableForFunctionReturn(node);
2394  bool isElementaryCast = false;
2395 
2396  if (IsContractConstructor(node)) {
2397  TranslateNewStatement(node, tmpVarExpr);
2398  } else if (IsTypeCast(node)) {
2399  TranslateTypeCast(node, tmpVarExpr, out isElementaryCast);
2400  } else if (IsAbiEncodePackedFunc(node)) {
2401  TranslateAbiEncodedFuncCall(node, tmpVarExpr);
2402  } else if (IsKeccakFunc(node)) {
2403  TranslateKeccakFuncCall(node, tmpVarExpr);
2404  } else if (IsStructConstructor(node)) {
2405  TranslateStructConstructor(node, tmpVarExpr);
2406  } else
2407  {
2408  VeriSolAssert(false, $"Unexpected implicit function {node.ToString()}");
2409  }
2410 
2411  if (!isElementaryCast)
2412  {
2413  // We should not introduce temporaries for address(this).balance in a specification
2414  currentExpr = tmpVarExpr;
2415  }
2416  }
2417  else if (IsVeriSolCodeContractFunction(node))
2418  {
2419  // we cannot use temporaries as we are translating a specification
2420  currentExpr = TranslateVeriSolCodeContractFuncCall(node);
2421  }
2422  else if (context.HasEventNameInContract(currentContract, functionName))
2423  {
2424  // generate empty statement list to ignore the event call
2425  List<BoogieAttribute> attributes = new List<BoogieAttribute>()
2426  {
2427  new BoogieAttribute("EventEmitted", "\"" + functionName + "_" + currentContract.Name + "\""),
2428  };
2429  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssertCmd(new BoogieLiteralExpr(true), attributes));
2430  }
2431  else if (functionName.Equals("call"))
2432  {
2433  TranslateCallStatement(node);
2434  }
2435  else if (functionName.Equals("delegatecall"))
2436  {
2437  VeriSolAssert(false, "low-level delegatecall statements not supported...");
2438  }
2439  else if (IsBuiltInTransferFunc(functionName, node))
2440  {
2441  TranslateTransferCallStmt(node);
2442  }
2443  else if (functionName.Equals("send"))
2444  {
2445  var tmpVarExpr = MkNewLocalVariableForFunctionReturn(node);
2446  var amountExpr = TranslateExpr(node.Arguments[0]);
2447  TranslateSendCallStmt(node, tmpVarExpr, amountExpr);
2448  currentExpr = tmpVarExpr;
2449  }
2450  else if (IsDynamicArrayPush(node))
2451  {
2452  TranslateDynamicArrayPush(node);
2453  }
2454  else if (IsExternalFunctionCall(node))
2455  {
2456  // external function calls
2457 
2458  var memberAccess = node.Expression as MemberAccess;
2459  VeriSolAssert(memberAccess != null, $"An external function has to be a member access, found {node.ToString()}");
2460 
2461  // HACK: this is the way to identify the return type is void and hence don't need temporary variable
2462  if (node.TypeDescriptions.TypeString != "tuple()")
2463  {
2464  var tmpVarExpr = MkNewLocalVariableForFunctionReturn(node);
2465  var outParams = new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>() { tmpVarExpr };
2466  TranslateExternalFunctionCall(node, outParams);
2467  currentExpr = tmpVarExpr;
2468  }
2469  else
2470  {
2471  TranslateExternalFunctionCall(node);
2472  }
2473  }
2474  else // internal function calls
2475  {
2476  // HACK: this is the way to identify the return type is void and hence don't need temporary variable
2477  if (node.TypeDescriptions.TypeString != "tuple()")
2478  {
2479  // internal function calls
2480  var tmpVarExpr = MkNewLocalVariableForFunctionReturn(node);
2481  var outParams = new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>() { tmpVarExpr };
2482  TranslateInternalFunctionCall(node, outParams);
2483  currentExpr = tmpVarExpr;
2484  }
2485  else
2486  {
2487  TranslateInternalFunctionCall(node);
2488  }
2489 
2490  }
2491  return false;
2492  }

2639  private void TranslateKeccakFuncCall(FunctionCall funcCall, BoogieExpr lhs)

2667  private void TranslateCallStatement(FunctionCall node, List<BoogieIdentifierExpr> outParams = null)
2668  {
2669  VeriSolAssert(outParams == null || outParams.Count == 2, "Number of outPArams for call statement should be 2");
2670  // only handle call.value(x).gas(y)("")
2671  var arg0 = node.Arguments[0].ToString();
2672  if (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(arg0) && !arg0.Equals("\'\'"))
2673  {
2674  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieSkipCmd(node.ToString()));
2675  VeriSolAssert(false, "low-level call statements with non-empty signature not implemented..");
2676  }
2677 
2678  // almost identical to send(amount)
2679  BoogieIdentifierExpr tmpVarExpr = outParams[0]; //bool part of the tuple
2680  if (tmpVarExpr == null)
2681  {
2682  tmpVarExpr = MkNewLocalVariableWithType(BoogieType.Bool);
2683  }
2684 
2685  var amountExpr = node.MsgValue != null ? TranslateExpr(node.MsgValue) : new BoogieLiteralExpr(BigInteger.Zero);
2686  TranslateSendCallStmt(node, tmpVarExpr, amountExpr, true);
2687  currentExpr = tmpVarExpr;
2688  }

2690  private void TranslateTransferCallStmt(FunctionCall node)
2691  {
2692  var tmpGas = context.TranslateFlags.InstrumentGas ? MkNewLocalVariableWithType(BoogieType.Int) : null;
2693  var gasVar = context.TranslateFlags.InstrumentGas ? new BoogieIdentifierExpr("gas") : null;
2694 
2695  if (context.TranslateFlags.InstrumentGas)
2696  {
2697  var callStipend = new BoogieLiteralExpr(TranslatorContext.CALL_GAS_STIPEND);
2698 
2699  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(tmpGas, gasVar));
2700  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieIfCmd(
2701  new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.GT, gasVar, callStipend),
2702  BoogieStmtList.MakeSingletonStmtList(new BoogieAssignCmd(gasVar, callStipend)),
2703  null));
2704 
2705  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(tmpGas, new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.SUB, tmpGas, gasVar)));
2706  }
2707 
2708  var amountExpr = TranslateExpr(node.Arguments[0]);
2709  var memberAccess = node.Expression as MemberAccess;
2710  var baseExpr = memberAccess.Expression;
2711  var retVar = MkNewLocalVariableWithType(BoogieType.Bool);
2712 
2713  var callStmt = new BoogieCallCmd("send",
2714  new List<BoogieExpr>() {new BoogieIdentifierExpr("this"), TranslateExpr(baseExpr), amountExpr},
2715  new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>() {retVar});
2716 
2717  currentStmtList.AddStatement(callStmt);
2718 
2719  if (!context.TranslateFlags.ModelReverts)
2720  {
2721  var assumeStmt = new BoogieAssumeCmd(retVar);
2722  currentStmtList.AddStatement(assumeStmt);
2723  }
2724  else
2725  {
2726  var revertLogic = new BoogieStmtList();
2727  emitRevertLogic(revertLogic);
2728  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieIfCmd(new BoogieUnaryOperation(BoogieUnaryOperation.Opcode.NOT, retVar), revertLogic, null));
2729  }
2730 
2731  if (context.TranslateFlags.InstrumentGas)
2732  {
2733  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(gasVar, new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.ADD, tmpGas, gasVar)));
2734  }
2735 
2736  return;
2737  }

2739  private BoogieCallCmd MkFallbackDispatchCallCmd(FunctionCall node, BoogieExpr amountExpr)
2740  {

2742  var memberAccess = node.Expression as MemberAccess;
2743  var baseExpr = memberAccess.Expression;
2744 
2745  var callStmt = new BoogieCallCmd(
2746  "FallbackDispatch",
2747  new List<BoogieExpr>() { new BoogieIdentifierExpr("this"), TranslateExpr(baseExpr), amountExpr },
2748  new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>()
2749  );
2750  return callStmt;
2751  }

2753  private void TranslateSendCallStmt(FunctionCall node, BoogieIdentifierExpr returnExpr, BoogieExpr amountExpr, bool isCall = false)
2754  {
2755  var tmpGas = context.TranslateFlags.InstrumentGas ? MkNewLocalVariableWithType(BoogieType.Int) : null;
2756  var gasVar = context.TranslateFlags.InstrumentGas ? new BoogieIdentifierExpr("gas") : null;
2757 
2758  if (context.TranslateFlags.InstrumentGas && !isCall)
2759  {
2760  var callStipend = new BoogieLiteralExpr(TranslatorContext.CALL_GAS_STIPEND);
2761 
2762  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(tmpGas, gasVar));
2763  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieIfCmd(new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.GT, gasVar, callStipend),
2764  BoogieStmtList.MakeSingletonStmtList(new BoogieAssignCmd(gasVar, callStipend)),
2765  null));
2766 
2767  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(tmpGas, new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.SUB, tmpGas, gasVar)));
2768  }
2769 
2770  var memberAccess = node.Expression as MemberAccess;
2771  var baseExpr = memberAccess.Expression;
2772 
2773  var ins = new List<BoogieExpr>();
2774 
2775 
2776  ins.Add(new BoogieIdentifierExpr("this"));
2777  ins.Add(TranslateExpr(baseExpr));
2778  ins.Add(amountExpr);
2779 
2780  var outs = new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>();
2781  outs.Add(returnExpr);
2782  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieCallCmd("send", ins, outs));
2783 
2784  if (context.TranslateFlags.InstrumentGas && !isCall)
2785  {
2786  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(gasVar, new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.ADD, tmpGas, gasVar)));
2787  }
2788  }
