2790  private void TranslateNewStatement(FunctionCall node, BoogieExpr lhs)
2791  {
2792  VeriSolAssert(node.Expression is NewExpression);
2793  NewExpression newExpr = node.Expression as NewExpression;
2794 
2795  // define a local variable to temporarily hold the object
2796  // even though we don't need a temp in some branches, the caller expects a
2797  BoogieTypedIdent freshAllocTmpId = context.MakeFreshTypedIdent(BoogieType.Ref);
2798  BoogieLocalVariable allocTmpVar = new BoogieLocalVariable(freshAllocTmpId);
2799  boogieToLocalVarsMap[currentBoogieProc].Add(allocTmpVar);
2800  BoogieIdentifierExpr tmpVarIdentExpr = new BoogieIdentifierExpr(freshAllocTmpId.Name);
2801 
2802  if (newExpr.TypeDescriptions.IsArray())
2803  {
2804  // lhs = new A[](5);
2805 
2806  // call tmp := FreshRefGenerator();
2807  currentStmtList.AddStatement(
2808  new BoogieCallCmd(
2809  "FreshRefGenerator",
2810  new List<BoogieExpr>(),
2811  new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>() {tmpVarIdentExpr}
2812  ));
2813  // length[tmp] = 5
2814  currentStmtList.AddStatement(
2815  new BoogieAssignCmd(
2816  new BoogieMapSelect(new BoogieIdentifierExpr("Length"), tmpVarIdentExpr),
2817  TranslateExpr(node.Arguments[0])
2818  )
2819  );
2820  // lhs := tmp;
2821  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs, tmpVarIdentExpr));
2822  }
2823  else if (newExpr.TypeName is UserDefinedTypeName udt)
2824  {
2825  //VeriSolAssert(newExpr.TypeName is UserDefinedTypeName);
2826  //UserDefinedTypeName udt = newExpr.TypeName as UserDefinedTypeName;
2827 
2828  ContractDefinition contract = context.GetASTNodeById(udt.ReferencedDeclaration) as ContractDefinition;
2829  VeriSolAssert(contract != null);
2830 
2831  // suppose the statement is lhs := new A(args);
2832 
2833  // call tmp := FreshRefGenerator();
2834  currentStmtList.AddStatement(
2835  new BoogieCallCmd(
2836  "FreshRefGenerator",
2837  new List<BoogieExpr>(),
2838  new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>() { tmpVarIdentExpr }
2839  ));
2840 
2841  // call constructor of A with this = tmp, msg.sender = this, msg.value = tmpMsgValue, args
2842  string callee = TransUtils.GetCanonicalConstructorName(contract);
2843  List<BoogieExpr> inputs = new List<BoogieExpr>() {
2844  tmpVarIdentExpr,
2845  new BoogieIdentifierExpr("this"),
2846  new BoogieLiteralExpr(BigInteger.Zero)//assuming msg.value is 0 for new
2847  };
2848  foreach (Expression arg in node.Arguments)
2849  {
2850  BoogieExpr argument = TranslateExpr(arg);
2851  inputs.Add(argument);
2852  }
2853  // assume DType[tmp] == A
2854  BoogieMapSelect dtypeMapSelect = new BoogieMapSelect(new BoogieIdentifierExpr("DType"), tmpVarIdentExpr);
2855  BoogieIdentifierExpr contractIdent = new BoogieIdentifierExpr(contract.Name);
2856  BoogieExpr dtypeAssumeExpr = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.EQ, dtypeMapSelect, contractIdent);
2857  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssumeCmd(dtypeAssumeExpr));
2858  // The assume DType[tmp] == A is before the call as the constructor may do a dynamic
2859  // dispatch and the DType[tmp] is unconstrained before the call
2860  List<BoogieIdentifierExpr> outputs = new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>();
2861  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieCallCmd(callee, inputs, outputs));
2862  // lhs := tmp;
2863  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs, tmpVarIdentExpr));
2864  }
2865  }
2866 
2867  private void TranslateStructConstructor(FunctionCall node, BoogieExpr lhs)
2868  {
2869  var structString = node.TypeDescriptions.TypeString.Split(' ')[1];
2870 
2871  // define a local variable to temporarily hold the object
2872  BoogieTypedIdent freshAllocTmpId = context.MakeFreshTypedIdent(BoogieType.Ref);
2873  BoogieLocalVariable allocTmpVar = new BoogieLocalVariable(freshAllocTmpId);
2874  boogieToLocalVarsMap[currentBoogieProc].Add(allocTmpVar);
2875 
2876  // define a local variable to store the new msg.value
2877  BoogieTypedIdent freshMsgValueId = context.MakeFreshTypedIdent(BoogieType.Int);
2878  BoogieLocalVariable msgValueVar = new BoogieLocalVariable(freshMsgValueId);
2879  boogieToLocalVarsMap[currentBoogieProc].Add(msgValueVar);
2880 
2881  BoogieIdentifierExpr tmpVarIdentExpr = new BoogieIdentifierExpr(freshAllocTmpId.Name);
2882  BoogieIdentifierExpr msgValueIdentExpr = new BoogieIdentifierExpr(freshMsgValueId.Name);
2883  BoogieIdentifierExpr allocIdentExpr = new BoogieIdentifierExpr("Alloc");
2884 
2885  // suppose the statement is lhs := new A(args);
2886 
2887  // call tmp := FreshRefGenerator();
2888  currentStmtList.AddStatement(
2889  new BoogieCallCmd(
2890  "FreshRefGenerator",
2891  new List<BoogieExpr>(),
2892  new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>() { tmpVarIdentExpr }
2893  ));
2894 
2895  // call constructor of A with this = tmp, msg.sender = this, msg.value = tmpMsgValue, args
2896  string callee = structString + "_ctor"; // TransUtils.GetCanonicalConstructorName(contract);
2897  List<BoogieExpr> inputs = new List<BoogieExpr>()
2898  {
2899  tmpVarIdentExpr,
2900  new BoogieIdentifierExpr("this"),
2901  new BoogieLiteralExpr(BigInteger.Zero) // msg.value is 0
2902  };
2903  foreach (Expression arg in node.Arguments)
2904  {
2905  BoogieExpr argument = TranslateExpr(arg);
2906  inputs.Add(argument);

3042  private void TranslateExternalFunctionCall(FunctionCall node, List<BoogieIdentifierExpr> outParams = null)
3043  {
3044  VeriSolAssert(node.Expression is MemberAccess, $"Expecting a member access expression here {node.Expression.ToString()}");
3045 
3046  MemberAccess memberAccess = node.Expression as MemberAccess;
3047  if(memberAccess.MemberName.Equals("call"))
3048  {
3049  TranslateCallStatement(node, outParams);
3050  return;
3051  }
3052  else if (memberAccess.MemberName.Equals("send"))
3053  {
3054  TranslateSendCallStmt(node, outParams[0], TranslateExpr(node.Arguments[0]));
3055  return;
3056  }
3057  else if (IsBuiltInTransferFunc(memberAccess.MemberName, node))

3059  TranslateTransferCallStmt(node); // this may be unreachable as we already trap transfer directly
3060  return;
3061  }

3064  {

3070  BoogieExpr msgValueExpr = null;
3071  if (node.MsgValue != null)
3072  {
3073  msgValueExpr = TranslateExpr(node.MsgValue);
3074  }
3075  else
3076  {

3078  BoogieLocalVariable msgValueVar = new BoogieLocalVariable(msgIdTmp);
3079  boogieToLocalVarsMap[currentBoogieProc].Add(msgValueVar);
3080  msgValueExpr = new BoogieIdentifierExpr(msgIdTmp.Name);
3081  }
3082

3084  {
3085  receiver,
3086  new BoogieIdentifierExpr("this"),
3087  msgValueExpr,
3088  };
3089 
3090  foreach (Expression arg in node.Arguments)
3091  {
3092  BoogieExpr argument = TranslateExpr(arg);
3093  arguments.Add(argument);
3094  }
3095 
3096  // TODO: we need a way to determine type of receiver from "x.Foo()"
3097  // This additional condition is checked in the loop at this call site
3098  // and was the reason why the code was not abstracted into a single call
3099  var guard = memberAccess.Expression.ToString() == "this";
3100  TranslateDynamicDispatchCall(node, outParams, arguments, guard, receiver);
3101 
3102  return;

3105  private void TranslateUsingLibraryCall(FunctionCall node, List<BoogieIdentifierExpr> outParams)
3106  {

3109 
3110  // find the set of libraries that this type is mapped to wiht using

3112 
3113  if (memberAccess.Expression.TypeDescriptions.IsStruct() ||
3114  memberAccess.Expression.TypeDescriptions.IsContract()

3232  private void TranslateDynamicDispatchCall(FunctionCall node, List<BoogieIdentifierExpr> outParams, List<BoogieExpr> arguments, bool condition, BoogieExpr receiver)
3233  {
3234  ContractDefinition contractDefn;
3235  VariableDeclaration varDecl;
3236  // Solidity internally generates foo() getter for any public state
3237  // variable foo in a contract.
3238  if (IsGetterForPublicVariable(node, out varDecl, out contractDefn))
3239  {
3240  List<ContractDefinition> subtypes = new List<ContractDefinition>(context.GetSubTypesOfContract(contractDefn));
3241  Debug.Assert(subtypes.Count > 0);
3242 
3243  BoogieExpr lhs = new BoogieMapSelect(new BoogieIdentifierExpr("DType"), receiver);
3244  BoogieExpr guard = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.EQ, lhs,
3245  new BoogieIdentifierExpr(subtypes[0].Name));
3246 
3247  for (int i = 1; i < subtypes.Count; ++i)
3248  {
3249  BoogieExpr subGuard = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.EQ, lhs, new BoogieIdentifierExpr(subtypes[i].Name));
3250  guard = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.OR, guard, subGuard);
3251  }
3252 
3253  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssumeCmd(guard));
3254  VeriSolAssert(outParams.Count == 1, $"Do not support getters for tuples yet {node.ToString()} ");
3255  string varMapName = TransUtils.GetCanonicalStateVariableName(varDecl, context);
3256  BoogieMapSelect mapSelect = new BoogieMapSelect(new BoogieIdentifierExpr(varMapName), arguments[0]);
3257  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(outParams[0], mapSelect));
3258  return;
3259  }
3260 
3261  Dictionary<ContractDefinition, FunctionDefinition> dynamicTypeToFuncMap;
3262  string signature = TransUtils.InferFunctionSignature(context, node);
3263  VeriSolAssert(context.HasFuncSignature(signature), $"Cannot find a function with signature: {signature}");
3264  dynamicTypeToFuncMap = context.GetAllFuncDefinitions(signature);
3265  VeriSolAssert(dynamicTypeToFuncMap.Count > 0);
3266 
3267  BoogieIfCmd ifCmd = null;
3268  BoogieExpr lastGuard = null;
3269  BoogieCallCmd lastCallCmd = null;
3270  // generate a single if-then-else statement
3271  foreach (ContractDefinition dynamicType in dynamicTypeToFuncMap.Keys)
3272  {
3273  //ignore the ones those who do not derive from the current contract
3274  if (condition && !dynamicType.LinearizedBaseContracts.Contains(currentContract.Id))
3275  continue;
3276 
3277  FunctionDefinition function = dynamicTypeToFuncMap[dynamicType];
3278  string callee = TransUtils.GetCanonicalFunctionName(function, context);
3279 
3280  BoogieExpr lhs = new BoogieMapSelect(new BoogieIdentifierExpr("DType"), receiver);
3281  BoogieExpr rhs = new BoogieIdentifierExpr(dynamicType.Name);
3282  BoogieExpr guard = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.EQ, lhs, rhs);
3283  lastGuard = guard;
3284  BoogieCallCmd callCmd = new BoogieCallCmd(callee, arguments, outParams);
3285  lastCallCmd = callCmd;
3286  BoogieStmtList thenBody = BoogieStmtList.MakeSingletonStmtList(callCmd);
3287  // BoogieStmtList elseBody = ifCmd == null ? null : BoogieStmtList.MakeSingletonStmtList(ifCmd);
3288  var falseExpr = context.TranslateFlags.OmitAssumeFalseForDynDispatch ? true : false;
3289  BoogieStmtList elseBody = ifCmd == null ?
3290  BoogieStmtList.MakeSingletonStmtList(new BoogieAssumeCmd(new BoogieLiteralExpr(falseExpr))) :
3291  BoogieStmtList.MakeSingletonStmtList(ifCmd);
3292 
3293  ifCmd = new BoogieIfCmd(guard, thenBody, elseBody);
3294  }
3295 
3296  // optimization: if there is only 1 type that we replace the if with a assume
3297  if (dynamicTypeToFuncMap.Keys.Count == 1)
3298  {
3299  // currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssumeCmd(lastGuard));
3300  currentStmtList.AddStatement(lastCallCmd);
3301  }
3302  else
3303  {
3304  currentStmtList.AddStatement(ifCmd);
3305  }
3306  }

3372  /// <summary>
3373  ///
3374  /// </summary>
3375  /// <param name="node"></param>
3376  /// <param name="lhs"></param>
3377  /// <param name="isElemenentaryTypeCast">indicates if the cast of to an elementary type, often used in specifications</param>
3378  private void TranslateTypeCast(FunctionCall node, BoogieExpr lhs, out bool isElemenentaryTypeCast)
3379  {
3380  isElemenentaryTypeCast = false;
3381 
3382  VeriSolAssert(node.Kind.Equals("typeConversion"));
3383  VeriSolAssert(node.Arguments.Count == 1);
3384  //VeriSolAssert(node.Arguments[0] is Identifier || node.Arguments[0] is MemberAccess || node.Arguments[0] is Literal || node.Arguments[0] is IndexAccess,
3385  // "Argument to a typecast has to be an identifier, memberAccess, indexAccess or Literal");
3386 
3387  // target: lhs := T(expr);
3388  BoogieExpr exprToCast = TranslateExpr(node.Arguments[0]);
3389 
3390  if (node.Expression is Identifier) // cast to user defined types
3391  {
3392  Identifier contractId = node.Expression as Identifier;
3393  ContractDefinition contract = context.GetASTNodeById(contractId.ReferencedDeclaration) as ContractDefinition;
3394  VeriSolAssert(contract != null);
3395 
3396  // assume (DType[var] == T);
3397  List<ContractDefinition> subtypes = new List<ContractDefinition>(context.GetSubTypesOfContract(contract));
3398  Debug.Assert(subtypes.Count > 0);
3399 
3400  BoogieExpr dtype = new BoogieMapSelect(new BoogieIdentifierExpr("DType"), exprToCast);
3401  BoogieExpr guard = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.EQ, dtype,
3402  new BoogieIdentifierExpr(subtypes[0].Name));
3403 
3404  for (int i = 1; i < subtypes.Count; ++i)
3405  {
3406  BoogieExpr subGuard = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.EQ, dtype, new BoogieIdentifierExpr(subtypes[i].Name));
3407  guard = new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.OR, guard, subGuard);
3408  }
3409 
3410  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssumeCmd(guard));
3411  // lhs := expr;
3412  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs, exprToCast));
3413  }
3414  else if (node.Expression is ElementaryTypeNameExpression elemType) // cast to elementary types
3415  {
3416  isElemenentaryTypeCast = true;
3417  BoogieExpr rhsExpr = exprToCast;
3418  // most casts are skips, except address and int cast
3419  if (elemType.TypeName.Equals("address") || elemType.TypeName.Equals("address payable"))
3420  {
3421 
3422  // skip by default, unless we have an integer/hex constant
3423  if (exprToCast is BoogieLiteralExpr blit)
3424  {
3425  if (blit.ToString().Equals("0"))
3426  {
3427  rhsExpr = (BoogieExpr)new BoogieIdentifierExpr("null");
3428  }
3429  else
3430  {
3431  rhsExpr = new BoogieFuncCallExpr("ConstantToRef", new List<BoogieExpr>() { exprToCast });
3432  }
3433  } else if (node.Arguments[0].TypeDescriptions.IsInt() || node.Arguments[0].TypeDescriptions.IsUint())
3434  {
3435  rhsExpr = new BoogieFuncCallExpr("ConstantToRef", new List<BoogieExpr>() { exprToCast });
3436  }
3437  }
3438  var castToInt = Regex.Match(elemType.TypeName, @"[int,uint]\d*").Success;
3439 
3440  if (castToInt && node.Arguments[0].TypeDescriptions.IsAddress())
3441  {
3442  // uint addrInt = uint(addr);
3443  // for any other type conversion, make it uninterpreted
3444  rhsExpr = new BoogieFuncCallExpr("BoogieRefToInt", new List<BoogieExpr>() { exprToCast });
3445  }
3446 
3447  // We do not handle downcasts between unsigned integers, when /useModularArithmetic option is enabled:
3448  if (context.TranslateFlags.UseModularArithmetic)
3449  {
3450  bool argTypeIsUint = node.Arguments[0].TypeDescriptions.IsUintWSize(node.Arguments[0], out uint argSz);
3451  if (argTypeIsUint && elemType.ToString().StartsWith("uint"))
3452  {
3453  uint castSz = uint.Parse(Extensions.GetNumberFromEnd(elemType.ToString()));
3454  if (argSz > castSz)
3455  {
3456  Console.WriteLine($"Warning: downcasts are not handled with /useModularArithmetic option");
3457  }
3458  }
3459  }
3460 
3461  // lets update currentExpr with rhsExpr. The caller may update it with the temporary
3462  currentExpr = rhsExpr;
3463  // lhs := expr;
3464  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(lhs, rhsExpr));
3465  }
3466  else
3467  {
3468  VeriSolAssert(false, $"Unknown type cast: {node.Expression}");

3483  public override bool Visit(UnaryOperation node)
3484  {
3485  preTranslationAction(node);
3486  BoogieExpr expr = TranslateExpr(node.SubExpression);
3487 
3488  switch (node.Operator)
3489  {
3490  case "-":
3491  case "!":
3492  var op = (node.Operator == "-" ? BoogieUnaryOperation.Opcode.NEG : BoogieUnaryOperation.Opcode.NOT);
3493  BoogieUnaryOperation unaryExpr = new BoogieUnaryOperation(op, expr);
3494  currentExpr = unaryExpr;
3495  break;
3496  case "++":
3497  case "--":
3498  var oper = (node.Operator == "++" ? BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.ADD : BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.SUB);
3499  BoogieExpr rhs = new BoogieBinaryOperation(oper, expr, new BoogieLiteralExpr(1));
3500  if (node.Prefix) // ++x, --x
3501  {
3502  BoogieAssignCmd assignCmd = new BoogieAssignCmd(expr, rhs);
3503  currentStmtList.AddStatement(assignCmd);
3504  currentExpr = expr;
3505  } else // x++, x--
3506  {
3507  var boogieType = MapArrayHelper.InferExprTypeFromTypeString(node.SubExpression.TypeDescriptions.TypeString);
3508  var tempVar = MkNewLocalVariableWithType(boogieType);
3509  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(tempVar, expr));
3510 
3511  // Add assume tempVar>=0 for uint
3512  AddAssumeForUints(node.SubExpression, tempVar, node.SubExpression.TypeDescriptions);
3513 
3514 
3515  currentExpr = tempVar;
3516  BoogieAssignCmd assignCmd = new BoogieAssignCmd(expr, rhs);
3517  currentStmtList.AddStatement(assignCmd);
3518  }
3519  //print the value
3520  if (!context.TranslateFlags.NoDataValuesInfoFlag)
3521  {
3522  var callCmd = new BoogieCallCmd("boogie_si_record_sol2Bpl_int", new List<BoogieExpr>() { expr }, new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>());
3523  callCmd.Attributes = new List<BoogieAttribute>();
3524  callCmd.Attributes.Add(new BoogieAttribute("cexpr", $"\"{node.SubExpression.ToString()}\""));
3525  currentStmtList.AddStatement(callCmd);
3526  }
3527  break;
3528  default:
3529  op = BoogieUnaryOperation.Opcode.UNKNOWN;
3530  VeriSolAssert(false, $"Unknwon unary operator: {node.Operator}");
3531  break;
3532  }
3533 
3534 
3535  return false;
3536  }

3538  public override bool Visit(BinaryOperation node)
3539  {
3540  preTranslationAction(node);
3541  BoogieExpr leftExpr = TranslateExpr(node.LeftExpression);
3542  BoogieExpr rightExpr = TranslateExpr(node.RightExpression);
3543 
3544  BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode op;
3545  switch (node.Operator)
3546  {
3547  case "+":
3548  op = BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.ADD;
3549  break;
3550  case "-":
3551  op = BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.SUB;
3552  break;
3553  case "*":
3554  op = BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.MUL;
3555  break;
3556  case "**":
3557  // Handled below for constants only
3558  // TODO: Need to introduce opcode for power operation
3559  op = BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.MUL;
3560  break;
3561  case "/":
3562  op = BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.DIV;
3563  break;
3564  case "%":
3565  op = BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.MOD;
3566  break;
3567  case "==":
3568  op = BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.EQ;
3569  break;
3570  case "!=":
3571  op = BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.NEQ;
3572  break;
3573  case ">":
3574  op = BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.GT;
3575  break;
3576  case ">=":
3577  op = BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.GE;
3578  break;
3579  case "<":
3580  op = BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.LT;
3581  break;
3582  case "<=":
3583  op = BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.LE;
3584  break;
3585  case "&&":
3586  op = BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.AND;
3587  break;
3588  case "||":
3589  op = BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.OR;
3590  break;
3591  default:
3592  op = BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.UNKNOWN;
3593  VeriSolAssert(false, $"Unknown binary operator: {node.Operator}");
3594  break;
3595  }
3596 
3597  BoogieExpr binaryExpr;
3598  if (node.Operator == "**")
3599  {
3600  if (node.LeftExpression.TypeDescriptions.IsUintConst(node.LeftExpression, out BigInteger valueLeft, out uint szLeft) &&
3601  node.RightExpression.TypeDescriptions.IsUintConst(node.RightExpression, out BigInteger valueRight, out uint szRight))
3602  {
3603 
3604  binaryExpr = new BoogieLiteralExpr((BigInteger)Math.Pow((double)valueLeft, (double)valueRight));
3605  }
3606  else
3607  {
3608  Console.WriteLine($"VeriSol translation error: power operation for non-constants or with constant subexpressions is not supported; hint: use temps for subexpressions");
3609  return false;
3610  }
3611  }
3612  else
3613  {
3614  binaryExpr = new BoogieBinaryOperation(op, leftExpr, rightExpr);
3615  }
3616  currentExpr = binaryExpr;
3617 
3618  if (context.TranslateFlags.UseModularArithmetic)
3619  {
3620  //if (node.Operator == "+" || node.Operator == "-" || node.Operator == "*" || node.Operator == "/" || node.Operator == "**")
3621  if (node.Operator == "+" || node.Operator == "-" || node.Operator == "*" || node.Operator == "/")
3622  {
3623  if (node.LeftExpression.TypeDescriptions != null && node.RightExpression.TypeDescriptions != null)
3624  {
3625  var isUintLeft = node.LeftExpression.TypeDescriptions.IsUintWSize(node.LeftExpression, out uint szLeft);
3626  var isUintRight = node.RightExpression.TypeDescriptions.IsUintWSize(node.RightExpression, out uint szRight);
3627  var isUintConstLeft = node.LeftExpression.TypeDescriptions.IsUintConst(node.LeftExpression, out BigInteger valueLeft, out uint szLeftConst);
3628  var isUintConstRight = node.RightExpression.TypeDescriptions.IsUintConst(node.RightExpression, out BigInteger valueRight, out uint szRightConst);
3629  // If both operands are literals, do not use "modBpl" for the binary operation:
3630  if (isUintLeft && isUintRight)
3631  {
3632  if (!isUintConstLeft || !isUintConstRight)
3633  {
3634  VeriSolAssert(szLeft != 0, $"size of uint lhs in binary expr is zero");
3635  VeriSolAssert(szRight != 0, $"size of uint rhs in binary expr is zero");
3636  BigInteger maxUIntValue = (BigInteger)Math.Pow(2, Math.Max(szLeft, szRight));
3637  currentExpr = new BoogieFuncCallExpr("modBpl", new List<BoogieExpr>() { binaryExpr, new BoogieLiteralExpr(maxUIntValue) });
3638  }
3639  }
3640  }
3641  }
3642  }
3643 
3644  return false;
3645  }

3734  new List<BoogieType>() {nestedKeyType}, bodyExpr);

3747  BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.EQ,
3748  idxNestedMap,
3749  new BoogieLiteralExpr(0));
3750  var qExpr = new BoogieQuantifiedExpr(true, new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>() {qVar1},
3751  new List<BoogieType>() {nestedKeyType}, bodyExpr);
3752  allocAndInit.AddStatement(new BoogieAssumeCmd(qExpr));
3753  }
3754 
3755  if (context.TranslateFlags.InstrumentSums)
3756  {
3757  allocAndInit.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(getSumAccess(currentExpr), new BoogieLiteralExpr(BigInteger.Zero)));
3758  }
3759  }
3760  else if (nestedValType == BoogieType.Ref)
3761  {
3762  if (context.TranslateFlags.QuantFreeAllocs)

3764  allocAndInit.AddStatement(new BoogieAssignCmd(derefCurrExpr, GetCallExprForZeroInit(nestedKeyType, BoogieType.Ref)));
3765  }

3767  {

3769  BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.EQ,
3770  idxNestedMap,
3771  new BoogieIdentifierExpr("null"));
3772  var qExpr = new BoogieQuantifiedExpr(true, new List<BoogieIdentifierExpr>() {qVar1},
3773  new List<BoogieType>() {nestedKeyType}, bodyExpr);
3774  allocAndInit.AddStatement(new BoogieAssumeCmd(qExpr));
3775  }
3776  }
3777  else
3778  {

3780  }
3781 
3782  currentStmtList.AddStatement(new BoogieIfCmd(
3783  new BoogieBinaryOperation(BoogieBinaryOperation.Opcode.EQ, currentExpr,
3784  new BoogieIdentifierExpr("null")), allocAndInit, null));
3785  }
3786  }
3787  return false;
3788  }
